title: butternut cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Beat 5 minutes at a high speed and
reduce
to low speed.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder; add
alternately with buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour batter into three 9-inch layer pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at
350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Butternut Cake Frosting.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press in oblong cake pan for crust.

title: cheese baked fish fillets
directions: Drain fillets on paper toweling.
Arrange in single layer in buttered, 2-quart, shallow baking pan.
Combine soup, sour cream and 1 cup cheese in saucepan; heat on low heat until cheese melts. Spread over fillets.

title: baptist muffins
directions: Mix water with cereals.
Let cool.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix alternating with buttermilk.
Add soaked cereals.
Add raisins and dates.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix above ingredients with a fork.
Place in small baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and cover with slivered almonds.
Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour.
Very good served on cocktail rye bread slices.

title: almond sauce
directions: Crumble cookies in water, stir until smooth; boil.
Add sugar, vinegar and mandarin juice, simmer for 10 minutes.
Finely chop mandarin and lemon, peel and fruit.
Add citrus fruit, peel, raisins, and almonds, simmer for 20 minutes.
Best with ham or pork.
Sauce freezes well.
Makes 2 cups.

title: layer cake
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco until light.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes three large nine-inch layers.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Put in casserole dish.
Add soups (undiluted) and Burgundy.
Mix well.
Cover and cook in 300° oven for 3 hours.
No peeking.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in oleo about 5 minutes. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook about 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink (about 10 minutes).
Stir in 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and core apples and slice.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan and place apples in bottom.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon and nutmeg and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: zesty cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans, parsley and bacon bits.
Shape into a ball; roll in pecans, parsley and bacon bits (your choice).

title: hash
directions: Cook hen and Boston butt.
Take meat off bone and grind or chip.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place in saucepan and let come to a boil.
Mix with meat as desired.
Sauce can be stored in a jar in refrigerator several days.

title: carolina dilled chicken(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Salt and pepper chicken on both sides.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and mayonnaise; add seasonings.
Pour over chicken covering well.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours for chicken with bones; 1 hour for boneless breasts.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine taco seasoning (dry) and hamburger until all hamburger is covered.
Toss together the seasoned meat, lettuce, tomatoes, kidney beans and cheese.
Right before serving, add dressing, taco sauce and crushed chips.
Toss well and serve.
Serves a large group.

title: lemon dill fish fillets
directions: Mix together salad dressing, juice, dill, milk and peel. Place fish on greased grill or broiler pan rack. Brush with half the sauce.
Grill or broil approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn and brush on remaining sauce.
Continue to cook about another 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with rice pilaf and fresh dill carrots.
Create a meal to remember.

title: wanda's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Add chilies, soups and enchilada sauce.
Heat through.
Alternate corn tortillas and hamburger mixture in lightly greased oblong baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: greek bulgur
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet.
Add dry bulgur; saute well. In a separate pan, saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until yellow gold.
Mix with bulgur.
Add broth, seasonings and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake in an uncovered casserole at 375° for 30 minutes. Adjust seasonings and stir.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
(This freezes well or keeps in refrigerator 2 days.)

title: chocolate parfaits
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine cocoa, cornstarch, sugar, salt and cold milk.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add hot milk, stirring constantly.
Heat over medium-low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool; stir in vanilla.
Place layers of pudding and whipped cream or topping mixture in parfait glasses to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Drain beans. Mix liquid from beans with soup mix.
Add a few spoons of corn starch to thicken sauce.
Toss beans and almonds with sauce. Heat until thickened and hot.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Bring water and soup to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5-10 minutes.
Yield 4 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Punch 3 holes in mixture.
In large hole pour shortening, in medium hole pour vinegar and in small hole pour vanilla.
Cover all with 1 cup cold water; stir well with fork. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost in baking dish.

title: awesome beef stew
directions: Brown meat on all sides in oil.
Transfer to large casserole dish.
Combine first 8 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add more if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients and bake about 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Thicken stock, if desired.
Serve with hot sourdough bread.
Delicious.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries.
In small bowl, beat together eggs, milk, oil and orange rind.
Add to flour mixture all at once.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when placed in center.
Remove, cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: In a slow cooker, combine the first 12 ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 6 hours. Add vegetables. Cover and cook on high for 2 hours longer or until tender. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: enchilada-style chili burros
directions: Heat together meat, gravy, enchilada sauce, chilies, onion, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer covered 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat. Use slotted spoon to lift meat from sauce.
Divide meat between tortillas.
Roll up tortillas; place seam side down in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Blend cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water; add to sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly; pour over tortillas.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes.

title: lime chocolate delicious
directions: Chill milk until icy cold.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and chill until partly set.
Whip until fluffy.
Stir in juices and sugar.
Whip milk, then fold into Jell-O mixture.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour Jell-O mixture over crumbs.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain, add cold water and bring to boil. Add soda, stir and drain again.
Put all ingredients in bean pot or pot large enough to hold all ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: fancies
directions: In small bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add extract.
Stir in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate raisins.
Shape into 2 rolls, each 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill. (Can make drop cookies.)
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: slush
directions: Use 1 cup of warm water to dissolve sugar.
Then add rest of water and all other ingredients together in large bowl or pan. Freeze.
After frozen, cut into squares and serve in ginger ale or Sprite.

title: white lemon cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add extract, sour cream and eggs. Mix in flour, baking soda and powder.
Chill dough 1 to 2 hours, then roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and frost with Oriental Frosting.

title: peachy french toast
directions: In a saucepan, heat butter and sugar on medium heat. Add water and continue cooking until sauce comes to a full boil. Cook 10 minutes, then pour into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Cool 10 minutes. Place drained peaches on top of sauce and cover with bread slices. Place them close together. Blend together eggs, milk and vanilla and pour over bread. Cover pan and refrigerate overnight. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. If mixture is browning too quickly, loosely cover with aluminum foil the last 10 or 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces and spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass dish.
Spread strawberries over cake. Mix Jell-O with 3 cups boiling water; stir well and pour over cake.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours.
Put Cool Whip over cake.

title: pate au chinois
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pare and cook chopped potatoes in water for 20 minutes; mash with a little milk and salt to taste.
Put aside.
Brown hamburg pieces in a 10-inch skillet; drain off fat. In a 2-quart casserole pan, layer browned hamburg, then corn, then mashed potatoes.
Bake in oven until bubbly and potatoes are lightly browned.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Tie spices in white muslin and place in cold water.
Boil. If water wastes away, add enough so as to leave 1/2 pint when done.
Add vinegar and pour over eggs.
Put in as many eggs as the mixture will cover.
When the eggs are used, the same liquid will do another batch or, after hard boiling eggs and removing shell, place eggs in a jar of beet pickle juice and the white will become red.
Cut in two to serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding and cold milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir until mixed.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers and bananas, sliced.
Pour some of pudding over this layer.
Continue until all ingredients are used.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Slightly cook broccoli, then drain; set aside.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pimentos, mushrooms and almonds.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Turn burner off and add peanut butter.
Toss cornflakes into mixture and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and cool.

title: vegetable patties
directions: Preheat pan to medium heat.
Melt butter; saute leek and garlic.
Add mushrooms; simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tomato; sprinkle with seasonings and simmer until liquid evaporates.
Add peas, pepper, spinach, basil and thyme; remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; allow to cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Form patties; refrigerate until ready to use.
Toast bread and place patties on toasted bread.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cheese until lightly melted.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix together 1/3 c. oil, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 large beaten egg. Add, mixing well, 2 cups quick oats, 1 1/2 tsp. baking powder, 1/2 tsp. salt, 3/4 c. milk.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour (30 minutes). Makes a delicious breakfast for adults as well as children.

title: fish poached in milk
directions: Heat milk in shallow pan until almost boiling, then add fish and simmer fish until flaky to fork.
Remove from heat.
Carefully transfer fish to a heated platter and keep warm.
Reserve the milk.

title: burger and macaroni skillet
directions: In skillet
cook
meat,
onion	and pepper until brown. Add remaining
ingredients;
cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: soft caramels
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan. Put all ingredients except vanilla in a heavy pot. Cook over medium heat, stir until it comes to a boil. Cook until 244°, remove from heat, stir in vanilla and pour into pan. Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Mix egg yolks and milk.
Add to dry mixture.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until set.
If desired, top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Pour into graham pie crust and smooth mix in pie crust. Top with cherry pie filling and then chill.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together boiling water, oatmeal and raisins.
Let stand about 15 to 20 minutes.
In large bowl cream together 1 cup white sugar, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Then add eggs; blend well.
Add the raisin-oatmeal mixture, flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: stuffed summer squash *
directions: In a covered pan, steam whole squash in salted water until tender. Drain and cool.
Cut lengthwise. Scoop out and discard seed portion.
Arrange shells in baking dish.
Salt and pepper shells lightly. Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients; toss well.
Fill shells with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown and squash is translucent.
Freezes well.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg substitute and pumpkin together. In a large bowl, combine flour, pumpkin spice, baking soda and salt. Make a well in the dry ingredients and pour in pumpkin mixture. Mix until just moistened. Stir in cranberries. Divide batter among 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pizza hotdish
directions: Brown meat, add peppers and saute, add soup and spices simmer.
Cook noodles per package instructions. Grease 9x13 pan. Pour in noodles, cover with meat sauce, then mushrooms and cheeses.
Bake covered 35 min. at 350 degrees.
Then bake uncovered for 10 min. more. Serves 6.

title: gumdropless cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: crustless broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9-inch glass pie plate with nonstick spray.
Steam broccoli for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp; drain well.
Set aside.
Put eggs, Parmesan cheese, milk, Cheddar cheese and cayenne in a blender and blend until smooth.
Saute onions in margarine.
Place onions in prepared pie plate.
Add reserved broccoli and pour egg mixture over all.
Bake for 20 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and outer edge comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and milk in a large saucepan.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Blend flour and milk.
Gently stir in mix and simmer until thickened.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook meat with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Saute onion lightly.
Add to meat.
Cook rice according to package directions and add to tomato juice, then add hot meat mixture.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 450° until bubbling.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pour
shortening into roaster.	Place steak into roaster. Combine
flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over steak.	Slice onion on top
of
steak.
Pour tomato sauce on top and water. Cover roaster and bake at 300° until tender.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in large, heavy pan and cover with water.
Then add chopped onion, coffee and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Check regularly and add water as needed.
Cook until fork-tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and more onion, if desired.
Add salt and pepper and noodles.
Cook until veggies are tender.
Coffee is a good tenderizer so a chuck roast can be used.

title: autumn pudding
directions: Mix
potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 1/4 cup margarine, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and pineapple.
Grease a 3-quart casserole and fill with mixture.
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Sprinkle on top of sweet potatoes. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind or chop tomatoes and peppers; add 1/2 cup salt.
Place in cloth bag, let drop overnight.
Grind cabbage, onions and apples. Mix with drained tomatoes and peppers.
Combine 2 cups sugar, 1 quart vinegar, 2 tablespoons pickling spice (tied in bag).
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and boil 15 minutes or until all vegetables have changed color.
Pack into jars; seal.
Makes about 20 to 25 pints.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be fried in cakes or put in muffin tins and baked at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter; beat with electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk, beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Cover and chill in freezer for 5 minutes.
Remove and spread with Chocolate Glaze.
Refrigerate.

title: apple bread
directions: Cut butter into sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend in vanilla and cream.
Add and stir in dry ingredients.
Add chopped apples and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour all at once. Beat well. Add flavoring. Pour batter into greased Bundt cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: english cookie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs well; add sugars and shortening. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoons full on baking sheet. Bake at 350°F for 10-12 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put everything in large pot.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste. Longer you cook it, the better it is.

title: texas salad
directions: Toss first five ingredients gently and sprinkle with crushed corn chips. Add dressing and mix well. Serves 12 to 16.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire, celery salt, salt, paprika, garlic and pepper in large bowl. Add chicken to mixture, coating well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Soak cabbage 1 hour, all covered in cold water.
Drain cabbage and cook it covered with other ingredients, except vinegar and the sugar.
Cook until tender.
Add vinegar and sugar and cook 15 minutes more.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a greased and floured pound cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fried lumpia(egg rolls)
directions: Cook and drain beef/pork; add shrimp. Combine all other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Place mixture in egg roll wrapper and roll. Fry in deep fat until brown. Serve with sweet and sour sauce or hot mustard.

title: brownies to love
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a large bowl.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, salt, marshmallows and put 1/2 cup of chocolate chips on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been generously greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all together and pour over crackers and mix well in large shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These are good with soups and salads.

title: meat, pork 'n beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Pinch bacon into little pieces.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in 13 x 9-inch glass dish or wide glass salad bowl at least 2 inches deep.
Serve with chips for dipping.

title: parmesan biscuits
directions: Add garlic to butter and dip biscuits into mixture.
Overlap 13 biscuits around outer edge of 9-inch cake pan.
Overlap remaining biscuits in the center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour.
Crush crackers; melt butter and mix.
Pour sugar and flour mixture on top of pineapple.
Pour cracker/butter on top, then cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-pear loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Stir by hand (50 to 75 strokes) just until dry particles are moistened.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan then cool completely.
To store, wrap loaf tightly in foil.
(Bake 45 to 55 minutes for 3 mini loaves.)

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet relish
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a large dishpan; mix all together.
Sprinkle with salt like you were going to eat it.
Mix good, then let set about 3 hours.
Drain off green water and fix vinegar mixture.

title: marinated garden vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix.
Cover bowl and chill for 1 to 2 hours and serve.
Serves 6.

title: crabmeat english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except English muffins.
Mix well.
Spread onto split English muffins.
Sprinkle with paprika (optional). Put onto a cookie sheet and freeze.
Once frozen, can be kept in a plastic bag.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; cut into fourths and serve.
Enjoy.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Slice strawberries and put powdered sugar on them; let sit 30 minutes in small bowl.
Mix milk and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip and 1 package of glaze.
Add strawberries.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Put a little mixture at bottom of bowl, half of cake, half of mixture and continue to layer.
Put glaze on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chill at least 1 hour.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Sift together in large mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the oil, eggs, carrots, crushed pineapple and vanilla; mix until moistened.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: low-fat broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together cooked broccoli, cheese and soup.
Place in baking dish and top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through and cheese on top is lightly browned.

title: as good as fudge(diabetic recipe)
directions: In small pan over low heat, stir together honey and peanut butter until smooth.
Remove from heat; add cocoa powder and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press into oiled 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into 36 squares.
Chill until firm. Yields 36. Serving size:

title: fruit shake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender for 30 seconds.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir in cranberries and chopped walnuts.
Combine egg, orange juice and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Bread is done when a cake tester comes out clean.

title: lots of noodles lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place cream cheese in a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl; microwave at High 30 to 50 seconds.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream; stir well.
Spread mixture over noodles.
Crumble beef into a microwave-safe colander.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Stir after 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes, giving dish a half turn after 4 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well the powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Add melted butter and mix.
Put in pan and pat down.
Melt chocolate morsels.
Pour over mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together and serve on crackers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and
part
of
Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.	Mix instant pudding
with
milk.
Spread
on
cheese mixture.
Top with remaining
Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Cut in half for 8-inch square pan.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Whip eggs with wire whisk.
Add sour cream and milk and continue to whip.
Place asparagus in pie shell.
Add cheese.
Add egg mixture.
Cut 1 tablespoon of butter into 4 parts and place on top of quiche.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 375° for 30 minutes until center is done.

title: fruity coolers
directions: Place 1 cup strawberries, half of the bananas, half of the peaches, 1/2 cup yogurt, 1/2 cup apple juice and 1/2 cup sparkling water in a blender. Process until smooth. Pour into tall glass, and repeat with remaining ingredients. You can also substitute your family's favorite fruits.

title: tallerine
directions: Cook noodles; set aside. Brown hamburger, onion, peppers and garlic. Add chili powder, salt and pepper. Line a casserole dish with half of the cooked noodles, then meat mixture. Cover with corn and cheese. Add last half of noodles. Over this pour soup and water that have been mixed together. Then pour Ro-Tel on top. Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250° to 275°.

title: herman starter
directions: Stir daily.
Five days later, feed again as above.
Then stir daily for five days.
Now he is ready to divide and bake.

title: jambalaya peppers
directions: Mix rice, tomato sauce, water and chili powder in 1-quart microwavable casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and ham.
Cut bell peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse.
Arrange peppers, cut sides up, in circle on 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Fill each pepper with about 1 cup mixture.
Cover and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes or until filling is hot in center.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and store in airtight container.
To use, mix 4 tablespoons to cup of boiling water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients to ground beef and mix.
Shape into a small loaf and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In a large
mixer
bowl
beat
cup margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half the flour,
all
the
brown
sugar,
eggs,
2 teaspoons of the vanilla and
baking
soda.
Beat on low speed until thoroughly combined. Beat in remaining flour. Stir in oats.

title: bar cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler; heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; beat 3 minutes with electric beater. Pour in containers.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix
in
Crisco,
sugar
one cup at a time, and beat in eggs one
at a time.
Add plain flour, milk and lemon flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw dough, but don't let rise.
Tear one loaf into pieces and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in pan and add rest of ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour over torn pieces of dough in pan.
Tear second loaf of dough into pieces and place on top, trying to fill in the empty places.
Let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn rolls out onto wax paper or foil while still hot and serve.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; salt and pepper. Cut onion into slices; put layer of onion in bottom of crock-pot, then a layer of steak pieces. Repeat layers, ending with onions. Mix together soup and water and pour over steak and onions. Cook 1 hour on high; reduce heat to low and cook for 7 to 8 hours. Add thickening to liquid to make gravy.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat the egg, then add oil and beat again.
Add other ingredients and stir.

title: luscious quick and easy processor cheesecake
directions: Using steel blade, crumble crackers into processor bowl and process until fine crumbs. Add butter, sugar and nuts.
Process until butter is well mixed into crumbs.
Line bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Pack firmly.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Freeze in large quart containers.
Thaw desired amount 1 hour before use.
Add 2 liters of 7-Up of Sprite per quart.
Makes 4 quarts or 4 punch bowls. Enjoy!
May freeze indefinitely.
Makes 24 servings.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Saute crushed garlic and sweet basil in butter.
Add heavy cream and cheeses.
Beat egg white and add.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Pour over cooked linguini and serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: no roll pastryhouston, texas
directions: Mix the shortening, flour and baking powder well with a pastry blender or fork.
Add boiling water.
Press pastry with hands into a 9-inch pie plate.
Do not pierce.
Use unbaked or bake at 450° until brown.
Makes 2 shells in smaller pans.

title: miracle icing
directions: Boil together the sugar and water for 3 minutes. Into a large bowl, place the egg whites and cream of tartar. Add the cooked sugar mixture. Beat 5 minutes. Add vanilla and spread on cake.

title: cream pie squares
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir mixture together until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine the salt with the cucumbers and let stand overnight. Drain. Add the onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour cold over the vegetables and mix well.
Put in jars.
Refrigerate. Stores in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: pulled maple candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it reaches full rolling boil.
Add vinegar, cream of tartar and butter.
Boil until brittle when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and pour out on buttered platter.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together making a fine batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine potatoes with milk, sugar, butter and seasonings. Stir in well beaten eggs.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Stir.
Bake 1 hour longer.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Place chicken
in bottom of Dutch oven or roasting pan. Cover completely
with
spaghetti sauce and add cheese on top. Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, (30 minutes for boneless chicken and 45 minutes
for boned chicken).
While chicken is baking, cook spaghetti.
Serve
chicken
on
side with sauce over spaghetti.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour tube or Bundt pan.
Blend together the ingredients and mix 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan and bake 50 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cooled cake.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Mix with mixer for 1 minute. Form 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet, mash with fork and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown; remove and enjoy!

title: hard candy
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken casserole(big recipe)
directions: Dice chicken. Boil rice. Mix with picante sauce. Add a can of corn and cube sharp Cheddar cheese. Put in a crock-pot. Serve when hot.

title: mexican cornbread #2
directions: Mix together well and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook salsa, beans and kielbasa in large pan until kielbasa is cooked.
While this is cooking, cook rice as directed on box. When rice is done, add to salsa mixture.
This is great with homemade bread or garlic bread.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Spread fruit on bottom of greased baking dish.
Spread cheese mixture on top of fruit.
Put in cold oven set at 350°.
Cook approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook together potatoes, carrots and celery 20 minutes in water to cover.
Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
In same pan used to cook vegetables, melt butter and saute onion.
Add flour, salt and pepper to onion/margarine; stir until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Stir in cooked vegetables.
Add reserved liquid, one cup at a time, until desired consistency is reached.

title: swirl chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat the sugar and cream cheese together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Measure 2 cups of the cheese mixture; fold in chocolate.
Pour remaining cheese mixture into well-buttered 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Add spoonfuls of the chocolate-cheese mixture and zigzag a spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool; then chill.
Cut in wedges.

title: bundt cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and water.
Add in cake mix, oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: he man dish
directions: Cook onions in oleo for a few minutes.
Take out.
Cook ground beef in pan where onions were cooked.
Cook until red is gone.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of noodles, layer of onions, and sprinkle thyme, Accent, pepper and salt over meat.
Mix milk with mushroom soup.
Pour over meat and noodle mixture.
Before baking, add cheese to top and pour beaten egg over top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cut vegetables in small chunks.
Mix together.
Add mayonnaise until creamy.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine
and
sugar;
add
eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla
wafers,
milk,
coconut
and pecans and mix well. You can start out
with
a mixer but becomes too thick and you will have to
use
hands.
Pour
into
ungreased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jackie's junk
directions: Mix cereal, peanuts and raisins.
Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter together.
Pour over cereal mixture. Put powdered sugar in a double brown paper bag.
Add mixture and shake thoroughly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Drop from a tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork that has been dipped in water. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Season to taste.
Add slaw and enjoy.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Brown beef and cook onion and pepper until transparent.
Mix all ingredients and cook 5 to 6 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: super salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes, onion and jalapenos into a 2-quart bowl.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk, marshmallows and chocolate chips in bowl. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Remove and beat together.
Put back in microwave oven on High 1 minute or until melted.
Remove and cool.
In bigger bowl, mix cooled chocolate mix and Cool Whip on slow with mixer.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Should be firm in 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Layer bananas, cookies and pudding.

title: taffy
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook to 265° on a candy thermometer (hard ball stage).
Pour onto buttered pans.
Let cool enough to handle.
Pull and stretch with buttered hands until almost white. Let taffy get completely hard.
Break or cut into bite sized pieces.

title: easy pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine, then add sugar, drained pineapple, coconut, vanilla and eggs.
Stir all of these ingredients together.
Pour into 2 frozen pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Melt 1/2 pound suet or 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of lard. Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Then add chili powder and cumin.
Let simmer about 1/2 an hour.
Add to the beans. If not enough soup, rinse chili pan out and add as much water as you need.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat water, brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Strain with cheesecloth and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and heat again. Pour into heated mugs and serve hot.
Used mainly at Christmas or New Year's Eve or after caroling.
Wassail means "be of health."

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 2 cake pans.
Split each layer and make 4 layers.
Mix remaining ingredients together well and when cake is cool, spread on each layer, making a four layer cake. Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: deviled green beans
directions: Mix butter and seasonings and heat with green beans.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
With electric mixer, cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Add flour and mixture and beat until smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped into sugar. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes, until edges are lightly browned. Makes 5 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: In medium bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat together sugar, liquid sweetener, egg and extract.
In a small bowl mix together dry ingredients.
Stir in the creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add water to make 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling, add gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add cola and fruit.
Pour into 1/2 quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with salad dressing or cream cheese dressing.

title: cannelloni
directions: To make stuffing combine the first six ingredients.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and milk. Cook in unbaked pie shell in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in roasting pan before mixing the sugar and other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix sugar, syrup and margarine over medium heat.
Bring to rolling boil, then cook and time 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over popcorn in roasting pan and stir well to mix.
Bake for 1 hour and stir every 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake into punch bowl.
Pour pineapple over cake. Spread pie filling and pudding over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple and nut spread(good healthy snack)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers or rice cakes, together in a bowl.
Spread on top of rice cakes or crackers for good snack.
Refrigerate after use.

title: hamburger vegetable chowder
directions: Add fat and brown meat.
Add all other ingredients and cook until all vegetables are done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix.
Form into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and bake at 350°. Do not press down on cookie sheet.

title: gazpacho
directions: Heat tomato juice to boiling. Add bouillon; stir until completely dissolved. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill for several hours.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and peppers.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients and cook for 30 to 45 minutes on low flame, stirring occasionally.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients using beaters. Serve with crackers and cocktail sauce.

title: light and easy green beans
directions: Rinse beans; snap off ends.
(Aaron needed this.)
Drop beans into boiling salted water in large saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, until tender, 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
While beans are cooking, heat butter in medium frying pan.
Stir in basil, pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes, turning lightly.
Mix beans with mixture. Salt to taste.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, molasses and salt.
Add eggs, cream of tartar and allspice.
Mix together.
Add flour, soda and raisins.
Add nuts.
Mix together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well (all ingredients).
Place in baking pan, greased. Bake for 30 minutes in oven at 400°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Grease 8 x 13-inch oblong pan and lay pieces of raw chicken on top.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup and parsley on top.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix together 1/2 C sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Place apples in bottom of greased 8 1/4x3/4 inch round ovenware cake dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.

title: chocolate chip pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Melt margarine and brown sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add sauce to dry ingredients.
Pour into greased pizza pan.
Sprinkle with chips and marshmallows.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until browned and done.
Kids love it!!

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped pecans.
Spread over bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over nut and coconut mixture.
Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese.
Stir in xx sugar.
Spoon over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until completely cool.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: date nut chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in nuts and dates. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken continental
directions: Coat chicken with flour; brown in butter.
Mix soup, onion, parsley, salt, thyme and celery flakes.
Add water.
Bring to boil and keep stirring.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Heat together chocolate, butter and milk over low heat, stirring constantly, until well combined. Add sugar and salt; continue stirring over heat until smooth. This is very good drizzled over angel food cake.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into serving pieces.
Dip in egg and flavored bread crumbs.
Brown, then put into a flat baking dish.

title: coleslaw dressing (creamy)
directions: Put in quart jar and shake.
For an entire head may double or triple.

title: venison delight
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic salt.
Coat venison with flour mixture.
Brown
in oil.
Place meat into a casserole.
Cover with sauce
and onions.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bear biscuits
directions: Separate biscuits; cut 3 biscuits into 1/8's.
Leave 6 whole. For each bear biscuit, round 3 of the small dough pieces, for the ears and nose.
Firmly press onto face.
Press in raisins for eyes and nose.
Add 1/2 cherry for each ear.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Enjoy with honey.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In 6-quart pan, saute onions in butter until translucent.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add chopped broccoli.
When it boils again, add egg noodles.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic powder and cheese.
Stir continuously until cheese melts.
Add milk and bacon.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking to bottom of pan until heated through.
Serve.

title: hamburger stuffed tomatoes with corn
directions: Cut the top from tomato; scoop out and reserve pulp.
Sprinkle inside of tomato with salt and turn upside down to drain. Meanwhile, cook hamburger and onion until its loses its red color, using a small amount of fat is necessary.
Add tomato pulp, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cook rapidly uncovered about 5 minutes or until liquid is evaporated, stirring occasionally.
Fill tomatoes with mixture. Combine corn with 2 tablespoons margarine, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Put into deep 9-inch pie pan.
Arrange tomatoes on top of corn.
Add remaining margarine to crumbs; mix well and sprinkle on top of tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread the frozen hash brown potatoes evenly in the dish. Mix the soup together with the evaporated milk until smooth. Pour over potatoes. Spread onion rings over potatoes. Cut the stick of butter into slices and dot potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix sugars, water and syrup in glass 2-quart measuring cup. Cook 7 minutes in microwave.
Stir in butter, pecans and vanilla, just until mixture changes to a slight creamy color, not long.

title: hot dill potato salad
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, dried dill seed, black pepper and salt.
Add milk all at once and cook until thick. Blend mayonnaise and onions and add to mixture.
Cook and peel potatoes.
Fold in mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: creole lamb chops
directions: Trim chops, dip in seasoned flour and brown lightly in hot fat.
Arrange in skillet.
Sprinkle onions over them and pour on soup and water, heated to boiling point.
Cover chops.
Bake in slow 325° oven from 3/4 to 1 1/2 hours until done.
Lamb steaks from shoulder or leg may be substituted for chops.
Serves 4.

title: peanut cluster candy
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips in microwave.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: greens with coconut milk
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 3/4 cup water to a boil over high heat.
Add collard greens, reduce heat to low and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add onions, tomatoes, coconut milk and salt; stir well.
Cook, uncovered, 20 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix sugar, milk and flavoring in a large bowl. Scoop new fallen snow from the top of a building. Stir snow into the mixture until it becomes thick and smooth.
It takes a lot of snow.

title: smores bars
directions: Arrange graham crackers in single layer in 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Spread over graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Cool on rack before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in large pot.
Heat and then add the remaining ingredients.
Stir good and simmer for 2 hours or more over low/medium heat.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat and bacon fat to make a marinade.
Put meat in deep container; do not use aluminum.
Pour marinade over meat.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate and preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes until brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hickory smoked chicken
directions: Soak hickory chips in water to cover for 30 minutes; drain. Adjust grill 3-inches from prepared coals. In small bowl, combine butter, salt, paprika and pepper. Brush both sides of broiler-fryers with butter mixture. Grill, skin side down, 20 minutes, basting frequently with butter mixture. Turn; baste well again. Place drained hickory chips on coals. Pull down door of smoke oven* to let smoke flavor broilers. Grill 20 minutes in smoke oven; do not baste. Serve smoked broilers with any remaining basting sauce. Makes 8 servings.

title: santa fe stew(servings:  6)
directions: Brown meat with onions and drain off fat when cooked.
Add seasoning mixes and stir.
Add rest of ingredients (do not drain cans).
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with crackers, corn bread or tortilla chips.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat and stir in water and stuffing mix.
Add egg and sausage.
Let set for 1 hour in refrigerator. Shape into oval balls.
Cut strips of bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around sausage ball.
Poke with toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: grannie's chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup.
Add all ingredients, except stuffing.
Mix.
Put in buttered 8 x 11-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add the other ingredients and refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour one 10-inch tube
pan
or
fluted
pan or 2 (8 x 1 1/2-inch) round layers or one (13 x 9 x 2-inch) oblong pan. Blend all ingredients in
a
large
bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 350° (50 to 60 minutes for tube pan or fluted pan; 38 to 40 minutes for round layers or 40 to 45 minutes for oblong pan). Cake
is
done
when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces.
Spread stuffing over each piece. Roll up and tie with string.
Brush with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in shallow roasting pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Put gelatin in cold water and let stand while egg yolks, sugar, milk and salt are being cooked to a custard.
Remove from heat, add gelatin, stirring until dissolved and set aside to cool. Add vanilla and beaten egg whites to cooled custard.
Fold in whipped topping.
Crumble graham crackers.
Mix with brown sugar and butter.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and mix or beat well.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk, nuts, jam, raisins and margarine.
Beat well.
Grease and flour pans well.
Can be baked in tube pan or make 3 layers in regular pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Caramel icing is good on this cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add karo. Beat eggs, salt, and vanilla well. When well mixed add the coarsely chopped pecans. Turn into a pie pan. Bake until firm at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Saute chopped meat and drain. Add the onions and peppers.
Add the tomatoes.
Drain the kidney beans. Add the Chili-O mix. Mix, stirring occasionally.
Re-cover and cook until thickened.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and water.
Add boiled mixture to the eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla and then mix with sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 16-inch flat pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Unbaked balls may be frozen.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Sprinkle taco seasoning on both sides of chicken breasts. Place the breasts in a 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Pour salsa over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: blended french dressing
directions: Blend onion and oil until white.
Add remaining ingredients in blender.
Chill.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water until tender.
Remove skin.
Debone and cut meat into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and cheddar cheese until well blended.
Add in remains ingredients except nuts. Shape into a ball and roll into the nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: party baked beans
directions: Combine beans, pineapple, molasses and mustard in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Sprinkle over beans. Top with 8 scored franks, brushed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: butterscotch morsels
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter over low heat.
Pour over the corn flakes and mix well.
Spoon out on waxed paper in small mounds.
Store in airtight container.

title: asparagus(serves 8)
directions: Scrape sides of asparagus. Cut into 1-inch pieces. Heat butter and cook asparagus for one minute.
Sprinkle with sugar and cook for 30 seconds.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and cook for 30 seconds.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad in this order:
Fill a large salad bowl half full of lettuce.
Cover with frozen peas.
Cover with chopped onions. Cover with chopped green peppers.
Cover with chopped celery. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover top with mayonnaise. Sprinkle top with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover salad and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: mock macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in white chocolate, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until pale golden.
(These freeze well.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add egg; beat until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into shortening mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Turn mixture into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, then clean.
Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap bacon (1/3 strips) around shrimp.
Use toothpicks to hold in place.
Put shrimp in large Baggie.
Add 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce.
Shake gently.
Put on cookie sheet.
Spread shrimp on cookie sheet.
Put in oven for 20 to 35 minutes at 250°, or until bacon is brown.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Cut washed, unpared eggplant in eighths and steam in water about 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain; chop fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased griddle and fry on both sides until brown.
Serve with tomato sauce, if desired.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat oil (3 to 4 inches) in deep fat fryer or electric skillet to 375°.
Mix remaining ingredients, except corn, with hand beater until smooth.
Stir in corn.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry until deep golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with maple-flavored syrup, if desired. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed but make 3 layers; let cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Put 1 layer of cake in bottom of punch bowl, then half of pudding, 1/2 can pineapple, 1/2 can cherry pie filling and 1/2 can fruit cocktail.
Then put second layer of cake and remaining ingredients.
Then put on third layer. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat; mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add milk and rest of ingredients well.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Melt butter in a deep dish.
Add uncooked rice, cover with milk.
Mix soups together and add.
Place cut up chicken on top. Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cover and cook for 2 hours at 325°. Do not peek during cooking time.

title: cocktail wienies
directions: Mix together in crock-pot and add wienies.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: With large spoon, mix dry ingredients.
Mix eggs and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Bake in 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a 3-layer cake. Bake and cool.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1/2 of beef.
Mix other ingredients together and chill.
Form into ball and roll in rest of chopped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: summertime fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute after mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Pour in pan and cool.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add bouillon cubes to hot water to dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on high for an hour, then on low all day.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti in 3-inch pieces.
Cook and drain.
To this, add 1/2 cup milk, eggs, grated Mozzarella cheese and garlic salt or powder to taste.
Stir thoroughly.
Place in greased jelly roll pan and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove and reduce heat to 350°. Place your sauce and any other ingredient you like (pepperoni, peppers, mushrooms, etc.) and then cover with 3 cups grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into squares.
Eat with a fork.
Enjoy!

title: tomato florentine soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven. Once hot, add onions, garlic and celery. Cook over medium heat, stirring continually until vegetables are soft. Add the dried oregano and thyme and cook for another minute. Add the chicken broth and tomatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; add frozen block of spinach and pasta. Cook at a simmer for 5 minutes; add basil and cook until pasta is al dente. Serve with grated cheese on top. Serves 6.

title: syrup pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup and shortening.
Mix soda in buttermilk. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to syrup mixture with buttermilk.
Bake in iron skillet at 350° until well done.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and bread.
Add mustard, eggs and milk. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 350° uncovered 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: italian spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: In a 6-quart pot, brown bacon until very crispy and dry. Remove bacon, leaving drippings in pot.
Brown onions in drippings until golden brown.
Add celery, garlic, bell pepper, green onions and parsley and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water, Kitchen Bouquet and bacon.
As soon as mixture comes to boil, add shrimp (or meats of your choice).
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Then add rice. Cook 10 more minutes before covering pot.
Cover, then cook on medium heat until rice is done.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes and pat dry.
Pierce in several places with fork.
Bake potatoes about 45 to 60 minutes until tender.
Cool slightly and then cut in half.
Scoop out flesh, leaving 1/8 to 1/4 inch.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer half of these and top with the following mixture:
1 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup pickle juice.
Repeat layers.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Scald 2 cups of milk and to egg mixture.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package. Heat the spaghetti sauce and keep warm while the pasta cooks. When pasta is done, drain and place in any large casserole dish or baking pan. Add the spaghetti sauce and stir. Sprinkle the cheese over the top. Place under a broiler until the cheese bubbles; this will be just a very short time. Be careful not to burn the cheese. Remove and serve.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl.
Pineapple juice, water and Sprite or ginger ale can be refrigerated beforehand.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Before baking, sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until center springs back when done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a banana right before serving.

title: tangy chicken quarters
directions: Brush chicken quarters with a mixture of melted butter or margarine and grated onion.
Grill, skin side down, 6 inches from heat, turning pieces often, 40 minutes.
While chicken grills, combine catsup, corn syrup, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in small metal saucepan.
Heat on side of grill.
Brush chicken with barbecue sauce.
Grill, turning and basting several times, 20 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender and well glazed.
Serves 6.

title: crazy pudding
directions: Mix pudding ingredients and put in greased pan.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture with zucchini.
Mix well; stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a little less with small pans.

title: mick's ham balls
directions: Combine and roll into 2-inch balls.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare a yellow cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven and make holes in warm cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Bring milk, sugar, coconut and coconut flavoring to boil and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour hot liquid over warm cake.
Cool completely.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.

title: easy cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients on medium speed until smooth. Stir in chocolate and nuts. Drop by heaping teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to cool. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Don't overcook.)

title: peach pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and water until thickened and clear.
Cool completely.
Pour over the sliced peaches.
Stir until well mixed gently.
Pour into pie crust and chill until set.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Stir in remaining ingredients until mixed.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice up squash and onion; add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until tender. Drain and place into large mixing bowl; add beaten eggs, cheese, milk, butter and crushed crackers.
Mix all together and pour into a well greased buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° for 1 hour. If desired, sprinkle 1 roll of Ritz crackers on top of casserole before baking.

title: my favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, then drain.
Then put in buttered baking dish.
Mix can of soup with milk and cheese; pour over macaroni.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until hot and brown, about 25 minutes.

title: fresh corn casserole
directions: Reserve 1 Tbsp. bacon drippings in skillet.
Add corn, green pepper and onion.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir in bacon, tomatoes and seasonings.
Spoon into greased, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "first place" chili soup
directions: Brown together ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves 16 (1 cup servings).

title: lazy pigs in the blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix hamburg, rice, soup (or onion), garlic, salt and pepper together.
Rinse sauerkraut lightly and mix in cabbage.
Add to meat mixture.
Mix tomato soup and water together.
Put meat and cabbage in roaster and pour tomato soup all over mixture.
Spread bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon dill potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 40 to 60 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half (long way).
Scoop out inside of potatoes, leaving potato shell.
Add all ingredients inside of potatoes.
Beat or mix together and fill in potato shells with stuffing.
Goes great with red meat, broccoli and a side of salad.

title: marsala braised veal chops
directions: Season the veal chops with salt and pepper on both sides.
In a large, nonstick skillet gently brown the chops on both sides in 2 tablespoons of olive oil.
Place the browned chops in a wide shallow baking pan.
Add the carrot, celery and 1/2 cup onion to the skillet and saute until lightly browned.
Deglaze the pan with the Marsala.
Stir in the tomato paste and boil for 3 minutes. Add the chicken stock, boil for another 3 minutes.
Pour this liquid over the chops, cover the baking pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add baby food and pineapple.
Set aside to cool.
Combine milk and cream cheese; mix with cooled jello and fruit.
Add nuts and pour into 9-cup mold. Chill well.

title: dog biscuits("pet food not people food!")
directions: *Get in health food store or substitute with oatmeal.

title: caramel-nut corn
directions: Divide popcorn and nuts between 2 ungreased pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cook brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges. Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn and nuts; stir until well coated.
Bake, uncovered, in a 200° oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: crock pot chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken parts. Roll chicken in flour and fry until brown. Put potatoes and onions in crock and add cooked chicken parts. Pour 1/2 c. water
over chicken and vegetables and cook until done.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Separately mix wet ingredients.
Quickly combine all ingredients so that hydrogen peroxide does not lose its strength.
Place in sprayed 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll dough.
Take casings off sausages and fry them until they change color.
Then spread on rolled dough.
Put cheese on and roll up like jelly roll.
Fold ends.
Let bake in 350° oven until it's brown.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix above ingredients through minced onions including the reserved marinated heart liquid in a bowl.
Add garlic powder, and pepper to taste.
Heat dip in microwave.
Serve with potato or tortilla chips.

title: guatamalan wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour, nuts and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough into small balls, 1/2-inch or so.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned. Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.
Cool.
This recipe makes 36 one-inch cookies.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water. Add a few potatoes at a time to bag.
Shake and coat thoroughly.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Melt chocolate and add to creamed mixture with vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into pie shell. Chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Shave chocolate on top or garnish with walnuts.

title: darn good jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add marshmallows and beat until dissolved.
Add softened cream cheese and beat well.
Cool slightly.
Fold in grated carrots, crushed pineapple, chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.
I sprinkle cheese on top for color.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain liquor from the oysters and put it in a saucepan; scald, then skim it.
Add the oysters and cook until the edges begin to curl.
Heat the milk just to the boiling point; do not scald.
Add the seasoning and butter to the oysters, then the milk.
Serves 4.

title: grilled vegetable medley
directions: Spread 1/2 of vegetables on sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Top with butter and cheese, then spread the other 1/2 of vegetables on top.
Season to taste with salt and teriyaki sauce.
Close up tightly with more foil and grill until done.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Then add molasses. Mix, then add all dry ingredients. Mix good. Gradually add boiling water. Pour into greased and floured pan, 9 x 9 or 8 x 8. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana salad
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil for 5 minutes except bananas and peanuts; cool.
Put banana, sauce and peanuts in layers in a baking dish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Cook in long pan; cut in 4 pieces.
Crumble 1/4 cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1/2 jar of pie filling and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Make instant pudding as directed on box.
Add 1 box to punch bowl.
Repeat procedure, then crumble last 1/4 cake, then the rest of filling.
Slice bananas over this. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Cover with coconut.
Top with pecans, then cherry halves.
Keep refrigerated. It's better to use 2 1/2 jars of pie filling.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put all ingredients in roaster.
Salt, sugar and mix in tomato juice.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of tapioca over top for glaze.
Cover and bake in 250° oven for 5 hours.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: turtles
directions: Combine caramels, milk and butter in casserole.
Heat on Full power for 3 to 4 1/2 minutes or until caramels are melted.
Stir twice during heating time.

title: yellow punch
directions: Prepare according to directions on cans.

title: layer salad
directions: Finely chop enough lettuce to cover the bottom of a rectangular Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle onion, pepper, celery and English peas over lettuce.
Combine mayonnaise and yogurt.
Cover the layers, sealing to edges of dish.
Sprinkle bacon over top, then cover all with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Can be made 2 or 3 days before serving.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap.

title: baked bean and hamburger casserole
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Add hamburger and brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients and put in a casserole dish to bake.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello and add sour cream and crushed pineapple with the juice.
Mix well (using an eggbeater).
Chill until set.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except sugar and peaches.
Pour over butter.
Mix sugar and peaches.
Pour over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix together ingredients; add to previous mixture.
Press into long, flat pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Mix all the ingredients together. In a 13 x 9-inch pan bake mixture at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12 easily.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add pumpkin and stir well.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours in a Bundt pan.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: Spread pecans evenly on a baking sheet and cover with butter. Bake for 25-30 minutes at 300 degrees or until lightly browned. Mix soy sauce, salt, and Tabasco and stir into roasted pecans. Let stand at least 30 minutes and drain on paper towels. Pecans will keep for months in a tightly covered container.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until just tender.
Blend in flour.
Butter toast; cut in 1/2-inch cubes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushrooms.
Add broccoli, soup, cheese and croutons.
Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with more croutons.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: diabetic thanksgiving cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup warm water.
Set aside to cool.
Stir together 6 packages Equal with graham cracker crumbs.
Add melted margarine.
Press 2 cups of the mixture firmly in 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve rest of crumbs for top.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake mix box.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan. While cake is hot, punch holes all over cake with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake while cake is still warm.
Let cool completely.
Mix cup of coconut (more coconut if you prefer) into Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cake. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato casserole with cherries
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: In soup pot, combine chicken, chicken broth and all vegetables and seasonings except corn and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add corn, cover and cook about 2 minutes until heated through.
Stir in lemon juice and serve.
Two grams of fat per serving.

title: house fried rice
directions: Cook onion, then put the oyster or soy sauce and meat into it. Then put the cooked rice.
Mix it all together.
Add scrambled eggs.
Garnish with green onions.

title: broccoli and cauliflower bake
directions: Heat soup and cheese together.
Put vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour soup/cheese mixture over and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: Peel off tough green outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut cabbage in half and take out core.
Slice thinly.
Julienne onion; cut carrot in 1/2 the long way and slice thinly on the width.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Toss the cabbage, onion and carrots in the oil. Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
After about 15 or 20 minutes, add the chopped garlic and season with salt and pepper.

title: french cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boil in saucepan.
Turn burner off and add flour to water.
Stir quickly until mixture forms a ball; remove from heat.
Add 4 eggs, all at once.
Whisk together until smooth.
Place mixture in rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cool. Slice tops off and save.
Fill puffs and put tops on.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: cheesy potatoes for grilling
directions: Cut potatoes like French fries; place on heavy-duty foil and sprinkle with seasoning and generous amount of cheese.
Dot with butter; seal in foil and bake on grill, turning a couple times.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: fried fish
directions: Allow for 2 or 3 pieces of fish for each person.
Rinse fish in lemon water.
Drain and sprinkle with salt.
Roll in flour and cornmeal mixture.
Heat oil to about 350°.

Fry in iron skillet with at least 1 inch of cooking oil on medium high temperature. Cook about 3 minutes each side or until golden brown and flaky. Serve with lemon slices, cole slaw, French fries, and hush puppies.

title: myrtle duncan's buttermilk salad
directions: Heat Jell-O, pineapple and sugar until melted.
Set aside to cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix dressing and oleo and put half in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Boil zucchini and onion for 5 minutes and drain.
Add soup, cream and zucchini, then put zucchini in cake pan and top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix and toss all together.
Butter a tube pan well.
Press mixture together in pan and refrigerate 1 hour.
Remove and slice cold.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Fry bacon crisp. Remove from drippings. Let cool and crumble in small pieces (save drippings). Chop jalapeno peppers into small pieces. Mix all ingredients and pour into an 11 x 14 baking pan or 24 muffin tins. Bake at 400°
until done. Will be golden brown.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Cut top off loaf.
Hollow out.
Bread cubes may be used to dip with, if desired.
Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf shell. Replace top. Wrap in foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serve with Fritos, chips or bread cubes.
Freezes extremely well.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half.
Remove yellows.
Mash with fork and add other ingredients.
Return to white portions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and stick of butter or margarine. Mix other ingredients and pepper and onion.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles well.
Delicious warmed over too.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk until it thickens, then add to cream cheese mixture.
Blend well.
Gently mix in Cool Whip.

title: pizza dough
directions: Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt in saucepan until warm. Combine yeast and 2 cups flour in large bowl.
Add milk mixture; mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining 3 cups flour until soft dough forms.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface.
Let rise, covered, in warm place for 3 hours.
Shape as desired.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until very warm, not hot. Spoon flour into cup and level off. In bowl, combine warm liquid and 2 cups flour. Add remaining ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. By hand, stir in remaining flour. On well floured board, work until smooth, about 2 minutes. Place in greased bowl and let rise in warm place until doubled. Punch down and put into 2 greased loaf pans. Let rise again. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk. Combine meat, onions, bread, salt and pepper. Shape into medium size balls.
Place meat balls in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crock pot sloppy steak
directions: Place flour in a large resealable plastic bag.
Cut meat into large bite-sized pieces.
Place a few at a time into bag and shake to coat with flour.

title: cheese apricot tarts
directions: Boil apricots in water until tender.
Chop fine and mix with sugar.
Melt margarine and mix with grated cheese.
Add flour, salt and red pepper.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
