Remove cheese dough from refrigerator and put orange size ball in microwave for 5 to 10 seconds.
Place ball between two sheets of wax paper and roll thin.
Remove top paper and cut dough into 1-inch size squares. Using knife, lift each square and put small amount of apricots in center.
Fold over two opposite edges forming diamond shape.
Bake at 225 until slightly brown.

title: sautee vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients into large skillet.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for about 30 minutes.

title: cucumber sauce(sauce from thailand)
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, boiling water, salt and chili paste. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients and serve.

title: honey iced chocolate(punch)
directions: Combine honey, cocoa, salt and mix.
Add milk and crushed ice. Serve at once

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and serve on lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Into a 9-inch pie plate, place a graham cracker crust.
In saucepan, melt large Hershey almond chocolate bar with water. Pour into crust and freeze.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove all dark skin, bones, etc., leaving only pretty meat. Mix egg, flour, onions, green onions and baking powder with salmon.
Should use enough flour to hold patties together. Deep-fry until brown or pan-fry until patty is brown on both sides.
This is a light croquette and swells due to baking powder. Do not use over a teaspoonful when deep frying!
Jalapenos could be added for those who have a hot palate.
Drain on paper towels.

title: green rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss rice and spinach together.
Add eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch, oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle butter and cheese over rice.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carob-rolled oat cookies
directions: Whiz dry rolled oats in a blender to make oat flour.
Mash bananas.
Combine all ingredients.
Make mounds of dough on nonstick sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Remove from oven before they appear done.

title: black-eyed pea stew
directions: Cook black-eyed peas in water to cover; salt to taste until tender.
Set aside.
Brown sausage in small amount of oil.
Drain. Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms until just limp.
Add sausage, black-eyed peas and tomatoes all together and simmer until well blended (about 15 or 20 minutes).
Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of dried hot pepper flakes to taste.

title: nana's zesty cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Dice sliced cheese very fine.
Mix all ingredients together with hands until thoroughly blended.
Shape into either 1 large ball or divide mixture into 2 smaller balls. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cover a sheet of waxed paper with chopped parsley (may use dried).
Roll cheese ball(s) in parsley until well covered.
Dampen and wring almost dry, a white paper towel.
Cover cheese ball with towel, then wrap a double layer of aluminum foil.
Refrigerate until firm.
When ready to serve, place on cheese board and slice.
Serve with variety of crackers.
This cheese ball will last for several weeks and the taste improves with age.
Makes great holiday gifts for friends.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; reserve liquid.
Remove skin and bones, keeping meat in large walnut-sized chunks.
Combine salmon and remaining ingredients with hands, taking care not to break salmon pieces. Add reserved salmon liquid.
Place in buttered casserole; set casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350°.
Serve with baked potatoes, green beans, cabbage salad and corn bread.
Serves six.

title: kathy's sunset turkey salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Stir in cubed turkey and mix well.
Cut apple into bite-sized pieces and mix apple and grapes into turkey mixture. Dice onions and sprinkle on top.

title: great northern beans
directions: Cook beans with half of the onion and celery until done.
Add tomatoes, pepper, oregano and cumin.
Saute the other half of onion in margarine until soft; add garlic powder and paprika; mix with onion well.
Add all to cooked beans, simmer about one hour. Refrigerate.
Better when reheated.

title: creamy hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, except corn flakes.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread corn flakes over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: m&m's pizza
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add soda, flour, cocoa and salt; mix well.
Add 1/4 cup M&M's, nuts and chocolate chips; mix. Spread dough on a foil lined pizza pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup M&M's on top before baking at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top and bake 3 to 5 minutes, until marshmallows are melted.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with whisk.
Add salt, butter, syrup, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: *May substitute blueberry pie filling.

title: sunday dinner strawberry cake
directions: Make according to package directions replacing water with a can of undiluted strawberry juice.
Pop top can found in beverage aisle at most large grocery stores.
Grease 9 inch round cake pans with Pam and dust with cake mix you set aside.
Bake according to package directions allow to cool completely.

title: macaroni salad supreme
directions: Combine macaroni with vegetables.
Stir vinegar into mayonnaise.
Add to mayonnaise and mix well.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add oil, buttermilk and slightly beaten eggs and mix together lightly.

title: nat's jiffy-apple dessert
directions: Put the pie filling into a 9 x 9-inch square cake pan.
Spread evenly.
Spread the cake mix on top of the pie filling.
Put 9 (1/4-inch) squares of oleo on top of the cake mix.
Sprinkle with the walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream when still warm.
Very good.
This can be made with cherry pie filling, too.

title: irish chocolate mint coffee
directions: Place sugar in a small bowl and sprinkle extract over it while stirring with a fork.
Thoroughly blend, then add remaining ingredients. Allow to stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally to dry. Store in tightly covered container.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with peels on.
Cool or put in refrigerator overnight.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Place bread, onion and milk over potatoes.
Slice the margarine and Velveeta and lay over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir melted cheese and butter into other ingredients.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over top and bake another 45 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, spices and jam.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to mixture. Cook in two layer pans at 350°.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Devein jalapenos and remove seeds (a potato peeler works well). Soak in water with 1 Tbsp. sugar for about 20 minutes and drain. Stuff peppers with Cheddar cheese.
If any remaining cheese, add to the raw pork sausage and Bisquick mix (which have been mixed together like a dough).
Put about 1 Tbsp. of sausage mixture in palm of hand.
Lay stuffed pepper on mix.
Put mixture around pepper being sure to seal, so that the cheese will not come out. Beat eggs.
Dip peppers in eggs and roll in Shake and Bake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine soda and water; mix well.
Cream the butter or margarine; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in soda mixture and vanilla.
Add flour, beating until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into 2 rolls (1 1/4-inches in diameter).
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Unwrap rolls, cut into 1/4-inch slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: red, white and blueberry delight
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and peel.
Mix well.
Stir in yogurt, marshmallows and nuts.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread half of the sweetened condensed milk mixture.
Arrange half the strawberries and blueberries on top; cover with remaining milk mixture and top with remaining fruit. Cover with foil and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 15 servings.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli. Top with chicken.

title: twity-bird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Mix eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts, bananas and apple.
Flour and grease a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(I bake at 325° for 55 minutes.)
Let cake cool and spread on frosting. Sprinkle on 1 cup chopped nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Measure ginger, pepper, garlic, lemon juice and soy sauce into screw-top jar and shake well.
Let stand 2 hours; strain. Score meat with 1/4-inch diagonal cuts.
Place in shallow 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Pour marinade over meat; cover and refrigerate 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain meat.
Grill over hot coals or broil 5 minutes per side.
Slice meat thinly across grain to serve.

title: claudia's punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add water to make 1 gallon and taste.
Add water, if too strong.

title: missouri casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, salt and sugar.
Cook at low heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Grease medium-sized casserole dish.

title: grated sweet potato (pone) pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in iron skillet or Pyrex dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 2 hours.
Stir about four times while cooking.
Last time, smooth top and let brown.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Place chicken in pan and sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion.

title: french vegetable casserole
directions: Dress peppers and cut in slices - peel onion cut into wedges. Peel and cut eggplant and zucchini into cubes or slices.
Peel tomatoes cut into wedges.
In skillet saute pepper and onion in the olive oil until soft.
Add eggplant and tomatoes.
Add minced garlic, thyme and basil.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover.
Cook over medium - low heat for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together Raisin Bran and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Butter muffin tins and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be stored in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: eldon's favorite crock salad
directions: Grind or chop cabbage, carrots, peppers and onions.
Add celery seed or celery and soak in salt water for 2 hours.
Drain well. Mix vinegar and sugar.
Put in covered crock or covered container or big jar; let stand in refrigerator.
The longer it stands the better it is.

title: potato collops
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into very thin slices.
Chop onion. Place a layer of vegetables in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings, parsley and diced bacon (rind removed), and dot with butter.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, finishing with potatoes.
Pour in milk and sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until potatoes are done and top layer is brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine eggs, vinegar and sugar in top of double boiler. Cook until thick and creamy. Add butter; mix well while hot. Pour over marshmallows, fruit cocktail and bananas. Fold in whipped cream. Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: wassail
directions: Mix and simmer at least 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chinese roast chicken or chuck
directions: Rub outside of chicken with ingredients except salt and ajinomoto and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Rub inside with salt and ajinomoto. Place chicken on rack and roast at 300° for 1/2 hour. Cover with foil and continue for another hour. Remove foil and raise temperature to 400° for another 15 minutes.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, oil, water and cocoa to boil.	Pour over flour and sugar.
Blend well.
Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk.
Pour into well-greased cookie sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Put first three ingredients in bowl.
Add peppers, celery and pimentos.

title: dried beef macaroni
directions: Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients and put in dish.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Cook and drain the green beans.
Saute the almonds in the butter until lightly browned. Add the lemon pepper seasoning salt. Toss almonds with the green beans.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, topping and egg.
Stir until well mixed. Dough will be stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls into confectioners sugar and coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Blend together soup and flour.
Add sour cream, carrot, onion, salt and pepper; stir in broccoli.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and melted butter and sprinkle around edge of baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6. I usually double this.

title: streamlined white bread
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and half the flour. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed or 300 strokes.
Scrape sides and bottom often.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.	Add ground beef;
brown completely.
Drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer one hour or until ready to serve.

title: stir-fry apple chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in strips.
Saute chicken in wok or frying pan in oil until cooked.
Remove from pan.
Saute vegetables; return chicken to pan.
Add apples.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt, soy sauce and vinegar well.
Add to pan and stir to coat while over heat.
(Mixture will thicken while cooking.)

title: magical mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa powder in separate bowl.
Add mayonnaise mixture to dry ingredients.
Add water and beat at medium speed until well blended.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool in pan.
While baking make frosting.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Mix and set aside the catsup and 1/4 cup water to pour over all meat loaf before baking.
Have boiled eggs ready.

title: zucchini bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Blend oil, applesauce, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together, then mix them in with the wet ingredients. Fold in nuts.
Bake about 1 hour until firm.

title: almond crunch candy
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch cake pan with aluminum foil.
Butter or spray with Pam very heavily.
Set this pan on hot pads or a heat resistant surface.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar; stir.
Add corn syrup and almonds; stir.
Boil, stirring constantly, until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 or 6 minutes. Working quickly, pour candy in prepared pan.
Cool about 15 minutes, or until firm.
Remove candy from pan by lifting edges of foil.
Peel off foil.
Cool thoroughly.
Break into pieces.

title: rush valley drought dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a cookie sheet.
Spread your favorite salsa on top of beans.
Add a layer of sour cream, a layer of smashed avocados, then sprinkle olives, tomatoes and onion over everything and top with cheese.
Scoop it up with nacho chips or Doritos.

title: marinade for pork
directions: Combine marinade ingredients and pour over chops.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil chops 8 to 10 minutes per side.
Brush occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until it spreads like butter.

title: wine baked pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Brown well in oil on both sides. Transfer to large ovenproof casserole.
Top with potatoes.
Brown mushrooms, peppers and garlic in drippings.
Transfer to casserole.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with oregano, sage, salt and pepper.
Pour wine over.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, shortening and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Stir in oatmeal, cornflakes and pecans. Use 1/4 cup mixture for each cookie. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken gravy(low-calorie)
directions: Warm chicken broth or defatted chicken essence in a saucepan over medium heat.
Place flour and milk in a small bowl and whisk until smooth or place in a jar with a tight-fitting lid and shake until smooth.
Gradually stir milk mixture into chicken broth or essence.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Add pepper, reduce heat and continue to cook, stirring, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 1 cup.
Serves 16; 1 tablespoon per serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a bowl, combine corn bread mix and onion.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Add to the cornbread mixture just until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes or until lightly browned and the edges pull away from sides of pan.
Serve warm. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let stand.
Pour boiling water over jello.
Add pineapple, cranberries, oranges, sugar and celery; mix.
Can add chopped nuts (optional).

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the soup and milk in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange half the onion rings in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with half the cheese then half the potato chips.
Repeat layers.
Pour the soup mixture over layers.
Cover and bake for an hour.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: catalina fruitcake
directions: Dredge raisins, dates and candied fruit in combined dry ingredients.
Add applesauce and butter; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and lined, small oat pans, coffee cans or cake pans.
Top with drops of brandy, if you like.
After cake cools, wrap in several layers of plastic wrap and let season for 2 months in refrigerator.

title: cauliflower eggplant curry
directions: Remove thick stems from cauliflower; separate flowerets and slice into small pieces.
Heat oil in large heavy pot with lid (I use electric skillet).
When oil is hot, add mustard seed and brown, covered.
Be careful not to burn.
Stir in turmeric, curry powder and salt.
Add cauliflower and stir to coat with spices and oil.
Add water and eggplant.
Parboil cubed potatoes separately, then add.

title: italian seasoned chicken(microwave)
directions: Rinse vegetables in strainer with warm water to thaw slightly. Place vegetables in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise. Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture. Fold chicken in half. Secure with toothpick. Arrange chicken on vegetables (thickest portions toward edge of casserole).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients; dip wiener into batter and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: iowa whoopie pies
directions: For cookies, beat shortening with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add about 1 cup flour, half the buttermilk, sugar, egg, baking soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining 1 cup flour and remaining buttermilk.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken 1 to 1.5 hours.
Let cool.
Break or cut into 1-inch pieces.
Grease a 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put into blender.
Let sit overnight in the refrigerator.

title: spanish sprout salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Combine lemon juice and pepper.
Sprinkle over salad and toss gently. Serve with commercial French dressing.

title: white clam sauce and linguine
directions: In a small pan, cook garlic in oil until tender.
Add clams with juice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook linguini and drain.
Pour sauce over linguini; add Parmesan cheese and a few dashes of pepper.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Chop
the
chipped beef and sprinkle on bottom of large baking dish.
Wrap
each
piece
of chicken with 1/2 strip of bacon
and secure
with
toothpick.
Place chicken over beef. Blend
soup and
sour
cream until smooth; pour over chicken. Bake
at 300° for 2 hours, covered, and at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: no cooking chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter; spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; beat well.
Spread over 1st layer and put in refrigerator and let set for 1 hour.
Next layer, mix pudding with milk and spread on 2nd layer.
Then top it with the rest of the Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add juice and beaten egg.
Mix well. Cook over medium to low heat until thick.
Cool.
Stir into prepared fresh fruit salad when ready to serve.

title: deep sea beef stew
directions: Remove any excess fat from stew beef and slice into small thin pieces. Brown it in a pan, adding a little meat tenderizer. Strain the fat out.
Add the recommended amount of water on mix packet.
Drain carrots, beans and potatoes.
Add the mix, carrots, beans and sliced potatoes.
Stir slowly on medium heat for 10 minutes. Stir in 1 teaspoon each of Mrs. Dash spices.
Vary according to personal taste.
Set heat to lowest possible boiling point. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes. Uncover and stir until desired thickness is achieved.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine milk, pudding, spices and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Beat and pour in pie shell.
Garnish with rest of Cool Whip.

title: caramels
directions: Mix well.
Cook to 242° stirring constantly over medium heat. (It will burn easy.)
When done, add chopped pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cool, cut and wrap in wax paper.

title: sugar-free bran and fruit cake
directions: Grate apple and carrot, add pineapple and juice together in a large mixing bowl.
Add the Raisin Bran and set aside to allow the bran to soften in mixture.
Beat in eggs.
In another bowl mix all dry ingredients, then add to mixture.
Spray a Bundt pan or loaf pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: crab casserole
directions: Beat 2 eggs slightly.
Add milk, butter and salt.
Mix together the flour, pepper and flaked crab meat.
Combine ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish.
Place bread crumbs on top.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake 50 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with champagne sauce
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning, until lightly browned, about 5 minutes a side.
Pour off fat from pan.
Pour cognac over chicken and ignite carefully with a match.
When flames subside, add chicken broth, champagne, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of the cream.
Simmer, uncovered, turning chicken occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Add remaining cream to sauce in pan. Bring to a boil and cook until slightly thickened, 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deer bologna
directions: Grind meat 3 times. Mix all ingredients together and place into casings. Smoke until it turns orange, cook in water until almost boiling, smoke again about 2 hours.

title: english cornstarch pudding
directions: In double boiler, scald milk, reserving 1/4 cup.
Mix together cornstarch, salt and sugar, using the reserved 1/4 cup milk to blend.
Add to hot milk.
Add finely shaved lemon rind and cook until pudding thickens.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to the rest and cook a minute or so, then turn into a dish and chill. Make pudding sauce.
Mix together the cup of milk, flour, sugar and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Flavor with lemon and vanilla and serve over chilled pudding.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Place in ovenproof casserole dish.
Combine pecans and butter in pan.
Saute lightly to mix. Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Better served warm.
Spread on Ritz crackers.

title: cream of tartar biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Dissolve soda in milk; mix with dry ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and handle lightly.
Cut in different shapes and sizes to suit your mood; try some different shapes.
For crusty biscuits, space them so sides do not touch on the baking sheets.
For soft sides, have biscuits closer together.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: crock salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Grind cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix all together and chill.
Do not seal.
Will keep indefinitely in open crock in refrigerator.

title: microwave potatoes parmesan(makes 2 to 3 servings)
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch dish in microwave.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Cook on full power for 5 minutes.
Stir in green pepper, salt and pepper. Cover and cook on full power for 3 minutes.
Gently mix in cheese and dust with paprika.
Microwave on full power for 3 minutes. Rest.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: lou's gumbo
directions: Dissolve roux and gravy mix in cold water.

title: beef tips
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Roll meat in flour and Lawry's.
Brown meat in oil; drain. Add enough water to cover meat; add thyme.
Cover pan and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour lemon juice over apples to avoid discoloration.
Melt cranberry sauce and jello in top of double boiler.
Add fruit and nuts.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Pour over flour mix.
Add zucchini.
Stir until all is moistened.
Pour into greased lightly floured (two) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or tested done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Complete cooling on rack.

title: corn soup
directions: Cook bacon crisply, crumble and set aside.
Cook potatoes and onion in salted water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not drain.
Stir in corn.
Add milk.
Heat until serving temperature. Serve with a melted pat of butter in each bowl and the crumbled bacon on top.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix margarine with cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of Tupperware "cold cut keeper" or a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: aunt helen's german potato salad
directions: Boil 15 salad potatoes with the skins until done.
Usually the skins will split when done.
Cool.
Skin potatoes and slice very thin.
Crumble cooked crisp bacon into potatoes.
Add bacon grease.
Add sugar to water and vinegar; stir until dissolved. Add to potatoes; add onion.
Mix gently.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Heat flour, brown sugar, butter and sherry until smooth and thick.
Layer fruit in bowl (Pyrex).
Pour sauce over fruit. Chill overnight.
Heat through and serve hot.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for about 1 minute.

title: italian spaghetti casserole
directions: Sear meat in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, hot sauce and chili powder.
Add mushroom soup, tomato sauce and water.
Put drained spaghetti in a large casserole. Pour meat sauce over it.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana oat muffins
directions: *Can use 1 cup oatmeal.

title: lemon delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together flour and oleo in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° until done, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Add raisins or whatever.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; gradually creaming thoroughly, add vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Mix flour, cocoa and salt together.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Yield:
7 pounds of batter, about 100 (2 x 2-inch) brownies.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Chill.
Keeps for 2 to 4 weeks. Excellent on warm breads, rolls and muffins.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Arrange four slices of ham over cheese, tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes about 64 slices.

title: snappy glazed meat balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. In skillet, brown meat balls, turning occasionally, and then drain. In small bowl, combine chili sauce and grape jelly. Pour sauce over meat balls. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm in chafing dish or electric frypan. Yield: approximately 4 dozen meat balls.

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Warm jello, pineapple (do not drain) and sugar.
Mix Cool Whip, baby food and cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in dish and congeal 3 to 4 hours.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl.
The following two mornings, mix the ingredients well and return to refrigerator.
On fourth day, form into rolls, place in pans and bake eight hours at 180°.
An alternative method is to wrap the rolls in foil, prick the foil and boil for 1 hour.
Let the salami set 24 hours before eating.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in pan; boil 7 minutes.
Pour over oleo and Marshmallow Creme, then add chocolate chips.
Beat and put in greased pan.
Cool.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel (optional).
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add the raisins. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes (until lightly browned) at 375°.

title: pancakes or waffles(buttermilk)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Stir in buttermilk and well beaten egg yolks.
Add butter; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter very gently. Drop batter by spoonfuls on lightly greased hot griddle; bake until brown on both sides.
Serve at once with your favorite syrup, honey or jam.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Open and and empty into microwavable dish.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Serve in bowls with fresh fruit or veggies.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add everything but tomatoes.
Cook 25 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes, or longer.
Then serve.

title: banana loaf
directions: Bake in loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Make in sandwiches with cream cheese, or eat plain.

title: vegetables parmigiana
directions: Heat oil and margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add vegetables and, stirring occasionally, cook 10 minutes or until barely tender.
Stir in salt, basil and pepper.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Stir garlic into tomato sauce right in the can; pour over vegetables.
Tuck Mozzarella slices into vegetables so about half of each slice is on the surface. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly and cheeses have melted.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook meat, celery and onions until almost done.
Add everything else and cook on low until ready to eat (probably 1 hour).

title: surprise stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, saute the squash and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bacon and egg potato salad(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: In large bowl, combine potatoes and onions.
In saucepan, combine ReaLemon brand, water, oil and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Pour over potato mixture; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving; add remaining ingredients.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Drain strawberries and pineapple.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Freeze.
Take out 1 1/2 hours before serving or put in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours and 1/2 hour out of refrigerator before serving.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and add instant pudding and oats and mix thoroughly.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Saut onions in butter.
Mix together onions, rice, soups and poultry seasoning.
Pour into 9 x 13 casserole.
Layer on top the cut up chicken.
Sprinkle the envelope of dry onion soup mix on top of chicken. Cover with foil and press edges tightly around the pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Don't peek.

title: beef, cabbage and bean casserole
directions: Saute beef with onion until beef is browned.
Drain.
Blend soup and tomato sauce with seasonings.
Stir in beans, cabbage, potatoes and beef.
Mix thoroughly and spoon into 2-quart casserole. Cover. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes and cabbage are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: angel muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly and fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until it sets, about 1 hour.

title: vinegar slaw
directions: Grate
cabbage
in
food processor or on a grater.
Mix sugar and
vinegar
together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then
pour over cabbage.
Chill several hours before serving. If serving with pork, add red pepper to taste.

title: kid's cinnamon buns
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Dip raw biscuit in melted margarine, then into sugar mixture.
Lay topping side up in pan or cookie sheet and add 1/2 cherry to middle.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix first four ingredients in punch bowl. Add 7-Up.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and press in long baking dish.

title: chocolate chinese noodle clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles (and nuts or raisins) so that they are evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill and refrigerate.
Yields about 12 clusters.
You may want to double or triple the recipe.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cut into pieces and place in 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth.
Heat to mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and butter.
Pour batter over chicken and soup.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Can be mixed the day before or just a few hours before grilling to blend the flavors. Very good.

title: paula's cabbage casserole(lazy man's cabbage rolls)
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery or you can use onion and celery raw and add with remaining ingredients.
Stir when it comes to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Stir frequently. Put in casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sunday roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Place in roaster pan.
Sprinkle onion around roast.
Mix gravy mix and water.
Pour over roast. Add cream of mushroom soup. Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover with lid and cook at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until roast reaches desired tenderness.

title: golden turkey bake
directions: Combine bread crumbs with melted margarine; set aside for topping.
Stir together the rest of the ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with topping. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine butter Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
At medium speed with electric mixer, blend well.

title: golden potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, blend soup mix with milk, water and mustard.
Add potatoes and toss to combine.
Microwave, covered, at High (full power) for 9 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles(sour)
directions: Soak the cucumbers in several changes of warm water to remove excess salt.
Cover with vinegar; let them stand 4 to 6 days. Drain.
Pack in hot jars.
Cover with fresh hot vinegar.
Seal.

title: baked fish in creole sauce
directions: Arrange fish in greased baking dish.
In a saucepan cook vegetables in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, vinegar, pepper, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture over fish and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: baking chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2-inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: chicken skewers
directions: Combine all ingredients to make a paste except chicken. Marinate meat for 1 hour. Saute 4 to 6 minutes.
Using 18 small wooden skewers, skewer the chicken, some green peppers (cut into 1-inch pieces), broccoli pieces, mushrooms, pineapple and onion pieces.
Barbecue or cook in a moderate oven for about 30 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: In covered kettle on high heat, boil brisket, bay leaves, onions, garlic and enough water to cover.
Simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.

title: baked beans
directions: In a greased 9 x 12-inch pan, mix beans, peppers, onion, syrup and brown sugar together.
Layer top with bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until bacon is browned.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add water and vinegar.
Cook slowly until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add salt and butter or margarine; then add beets.
Cover and continue cooking about 10 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: frozen alaskan salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Whip whipping cream until almost stiff, then (gradually) beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold whipped cream into cranberry/cheese mixture; freeze.
Cut into squares.
Serve frozen.

title: mexican meatball soup
directions: Saute the carrots and onion in the olive oil.
Add the chicken stock, water, consomme and tomato sauce.
Simmer over low flame for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix the beef, rice, egg, parsley, salt and pepper together to form small meat balls.
Bring the soup to a boil; add the meat balls, lower flame and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add the peas and cilantro and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onions in their round slices; cut pepper in small slices.
Mix with carrots. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables. Cover. Marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Drain and serve.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: jello cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Bake 9 x 13-inch cake at 350°.
Make jello according to package directions.
While cake is hot, make holes in cake with a fork and pour hot jello over.
Make topping with whipping cream and fruit cocktail.
Put on after cake is cooled.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, bread crumbs and seasoning in one bowl.
Place beaten eggs into another bowl.
Dip chicken pieces first in egg and then in flour mixture.
Let stand for about 1 hour.
Fry chicken pieces in a mixture of butter and Crisco until golden in color.
Place chicken pieces in a buttered pan, covered with foil, and bake in 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil after 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon in pan and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water by hand. Add other ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Coat nuts with mixture.
Melt butter in pan; put mixture on top of butter. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Turn several times.

title: reese's cup
directions: Melt the Hershey bar and 1/2 cup peanut butter together.
In separate pan, melt the other half of the peanut butter.
Put 1 tablespoon melted chocolate mixture in cupcake paper.
Let firm. Next, put 1 tablespoon peanut butter; let firm.
Top with 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture.
Let firm.
Enjoy.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt. Then mix all of the other ingredients and pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine (can also add celery).
Add cooked squash, chicken soup and sour cream.
Butter oblong baking dish and spoon in half the stuffing mix.
Put squash mixture over stuffing and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple daisy
directions: Arrange each cinnamon roll in a round cake pan.
Dip each apple slice in melted butter, then in the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Then, place an apple slice in between each roll on all sides and around the outer edges.
Bake according to package directions.
Top with icing included in the cinnamon roll can and enjoy!

title: butternut squash soup
directions: *Use equal amounts of potatoes and squash.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice in 2 cups water.
Brown pork sausage and drain off drippings.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix together water chestnuts (sliced and drained), mushroom soup, 1 soup can of water, almonds, mushrooms, celery salt, garlic salt, pepper, onion salt, paprika and salt.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until tender. Remove from heat and add cream cheese, milk, butter, Cream of Celery soup, Mushroom soup, garlic salt, and salt and pepper. Simmer about 10 minutes. Heat soup again when serving. Add bacon bits, shredded cheese and green onions to individual servings if desired.

title: toot's biscuits
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix and sift dry ingredients.
Place the Crisco shortening into the flour mix. Start working the shortening through the flour mix very thoroughly.
Pour milk gradually into the well mixed flour and shortening until the ingredients have become gummy.
From the bag of flour, sprinkle flour very thoroughly through the gummy dough. Work the flour through the dough until the dough is no longer gummy.
Roll the dough out on a chopping board.
Use a medium size glass to cut out the biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: easy pot roast
directions: In hot 12-inch	Dutch oven pour in oil and brown roast. Drain off oil.
Add
soup
mix, canned soup, carrots and potatoes.
Cook covered
for
hours
with 12 coals on the bottom only. Replenish coals as necessary.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; mash and add the remaining ingredients. Put in casserole dish.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil and eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 13-inch round baking pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: In a large bowl combine first four ingredients. Chill. Place in a punch bowl. Add chunks of sherbet. Garnish with orange slices. Serves 20.

title: pineapple-zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to batter.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and raisins (if desired).
Mix well.
Turn into pans and bake 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack before removing from pans.
Wrap and store overnight to develop flavor before slicing.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a large (10-inch) pie (or quiche) pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white grape punch
directions: Mix and serve chilled.

title: crock-pot chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts (boned) in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Mix other ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cook 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix and put in freezer and freeze.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix together and then roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Makes about 16.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet, adding salt and pepper to taste. Drain grease and cover chops with tomato sauce.
Throw in whatever else you want to, such as Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, etc. Cover and cook over low heat until chops are tender.

title: savory beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook for 1 hour after coming to a boil. Drain and save water.
Add sugar, mustard and soup, then fry bacon.
Add fat and bacon to bean mix.
Bake 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Let stand.

title: pineapple prize muffins
directions: Turn pineapple into wire strainer and drain. Combine flours, wheat germ, sugar, coconut, nuts, baking soda and salt. In a separate bowl, combine drained pineapple, yogurt, eggs and oil. Mix well. Add to dry mixture. Stir lightly just until all of the dry mixture is moistened.
Spoon into greased or paper lined muffin pans (2 3/4-inch diameter), filling 3/4 full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 15 to 18 muffins.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut into bite size pieces. Mix soups together. Drain vegetables and add to soup mixture. May use 2 cans of mixed peas and carrots instead of 1 can of each. Add chicken and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs, then add milk, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into prepared 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Wash lemon, leaving peel on cut into small pieces. Remove seeds and discard. Place lemon pieces in blender container. Blend on high. Add eggs, sugar and margarine or butter. Process well on high speed. Pour into unbaked pie shell and place pie pan on baking sheet. Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until set. Remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: phyllis lahey's butter horns
directions: Sift flour, 2 tablespoon sugar and salt together.
Add butter and work until mealy.
Scald milk; add 2 teaspoons sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Beat egg yolks. Add cream and cardamon; mix well.
Stir into flour mixture to make a smooth dough.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: cheese squares
directions: Blend all ingredients, except bread.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Layer 3 slices high.
Cut into 4 squares and spread cheese mixture on top and sides.
Put on tray or cookie sheet to freeze.
When frozen, store in plastic bags until ready to use.

title: flavored olive oil
directions: Wash the rosemary if you must; dry thoroughly.
(Oil and water do not mix.)
In a 17-ounce bottle of olive oil, add the first 3 ingredients.
Shake well before use.
Use on anything for which you use olive oil.
Do not store in the refrigerator.

title: barbecued squirrel
directions: Rub pieces of squirrel with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour. Pan-fry to form crust.
Remove pieces from skillet and place in casserole.
Add chopped onion to suit taste.
Pour barbecue sauce over all.
Cover and finish cooking in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla pudding together. In a large bowl, layer as follows:
layer of crushed graham crackers, Cool Whip mixture and layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat layers.

title: grape  nut salad
directions: Cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, and vanilla together, then add nuts;
stir well.
Add grapes.
Chill before serving.

title: kentucky butter cake(makes 10-inch tube cake.)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Add alternately with the dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
(With electric mixer, use low speed.)
Turn into 10-inch tube pan, greased on the bottom.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes until cake springs back when touched in center.
Run spatula along edge and stem of pan.
Prick cake with fork.
Pour hot Sauce over cake.
Cool before removing from pan.
Just before serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cake may be baked in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Cook until light brown. Mix cream cheese and sugar together until creamy.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cookie dough.
Decorate with whatever kind of fruit (canned) you like.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop from tip of spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
(Keep back a small amount of coconut to sprinkle on top of macaroons before baking. I always double recipe.)

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let stand until yeast is dissolved and growing.
Gradually add the rest of the items and only 1 cup of flour at a time until the dough doesn't stick to hands; knead 5 minutes.
Rub a small amount of Crisco on surface and cover in warm place.
Let rise 1 hour.
Roll a small amount at a time about 1/8-inch thick and cut 3-inch or 4-inch squares.
Fry in hot oil until golden and pillowy.
Serve hot with honey, sugar and cinnamon.

title: batter bread
directions: Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
Add egg and stir well. Add warm milk. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add rolled wheat or oatmeal to flour.
Add slowly to yeast mixture, stirring well.
Spread mixture in pan. Brush top with melted butter. Sprinkle with dry oatmeal.
Let rise until double in height (about 1 hour).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares (may brush top with melted butter).
Serve hot.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: parish pasta salad
directions: Follow directions on pasta salad boxes to cook pasta. Brown ground beef. Remove from skillet, then brown sausage. Drain and return both beef and sausage. Add garlic. Mix cooked pasta in salad bowl with olive oil. Add 1/3 to 1/2 of the seasoning mix from each box (taste for your preference for seasoning). Add meat and mix well. Break the snow peas into bite size pieces after you've washed and capped them.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Place butter, eggs, sugar and cream cheese in a large bowl. Beat with electric mixer for 10 to 15 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder; beat 3 minutes more.

title: party meatballs
directions: Wash hands.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in mixing bowl the hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, seasonings and herbs of choice. Bake small meatballs on cookie sheet (20 minutes).

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh cut vegetables.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Place tortilla chips in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with chicken and set aside. In a saucepan over low heat, combine cheese, Ro-Tel, soups and cumin. Heat until cheese melts. Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly while cooking, until thickened.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir into thickened mixture.
Cook another five minutes. Add vanilla.
Set aside.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers.
Add layer of sliced bananas.
Pour pudding mixture over top.
Top with meringue after pudding has cooled.

title: corned beef hash
directions: (Note:	Amount of potatoes, carrots and onions will depend on amount of meat).

title: chocolate in-betweens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add brown sugar, butter and salt.
Mix together.
Add flour and oats to mixture.
Mix until crumbly. Press about 2/3 of mixture (2 1/2 cups) into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Leave remaining 1/3 mixture in bowl.

title: mammaw tynes' chili
directions: Brown the hamburger meat; add the onion.
Drain fat.
Add the tomatoes, water and chili seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add the beans and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: mary's chicken curry
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Drain grease, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook celery, onion and garlic in drippings, blending in flour.
Stir in milk, water, applesauce, tomato paste, crushed bouillon and curry powder. Stir in chicken and bacon.
Serve over rice.
(I use near East Rice pilaf.)

Also serve small bowls of condiments to sprinkle on top including shredded coconut, cashew pieces, unsalted peanuts, mango chutney, dark raisins, golden raisins, dried apricot pieces, diced green and red pepper and almond slivers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 8-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes. Then cool and frost.

title: joe's pork barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to rolling boil.
After hog is turned with skin side down, apply sauce and cook until all sauce is absorbed.

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Crush 1 cup of corn flakes; place in a large mixing bowl.
Add egg, tomatoes, salt and pepper; beat well.
Add ground beef; mix only until combined.
Shape into 6 loaves, about 4 inches long. Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each loaf with 1/2 slice of cheese.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: quick and easy french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip bread in mixture and brown on both sides in hot butter skillet.
Use butter and your favorite syrup on top.

title: shrimp florentine
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Set aside to drain on paper towels. Thaw spinach.
Press out as much water as possible. Make a white sauce of flour, milk and Butter Buds. Stir in Egg Beaters.
Heat.
The sauce should be thick.
If not, thicken before proceeding.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add nutmeg, parsley and onion. Stir in well-drained spinach.
Spray a shallow baking dish with Pam.
Put 3/4 of spinach mixture in the dish.
Arrange raw shrimp on top in a decorative pattern.
Garnish with remaining sauce, taking care to leave some of the shrimp exposed.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
The sauce should be bubbling, the shrimp pink. Overcooking will make the shrimp tough.

title: blueberry cake with cinnamon topping
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft.
Beat in egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla until blended.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder. Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: yankee salad
directions: Fold together and chill.
This is good for days.
Serve with your meal or as a dessert.

title: fastnachts(grace church, shrove tuesday)
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve dry yeast in water.
Add to lukewarm milk, egg and half of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter (no hole in center).
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk. Fry in deep lard, 375° for 2 to 3 minutes until both sides are golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
While warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli, peanuts, raisins, onion and bacon.
Mix well.

title: spaghetti with pesto
directions: Wash and dry the basil and remove stems.
Place it in a blender with the garlic, olive oil, pine nuts, butter and cheese. Puree.

title: biscotti-italian dunking cookies
directions: Beat egg, sugar and anise well.
Add flour, then add almonds. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spread on oiled wax paper.
When baked, flip over and take wax paper off and cut in strips about 1 inch thick and cut each strip in 4 or 5 pieces.
Put back on pan and bake until toasted well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth.
Add chopped pecans and grated carrots.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1/2-inch chunks.
Coat thoroughly with flour. Brown in skillet with oil about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Dissolve cornstarch in vinegar; stir in chili sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Add to pork with apricot jelly.
Heat to boiling. Turn heat down.
Add peppers.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in oranges and pineapple.
Heat 2 minutes more.

title: tangy italian cheese bread
directions: Place bread slices on a broiler rack.
Brush top of each slice lightly with salad dressing.
Sprinkle cheese, parsley and basil evenly over bread.
Broil 6-inches from heat, until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream until blended.
Add hot potatoes, beating slowly until light and fluffy.
Season with onion salt and garlic powder.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar well, then toss with salad. Refrigerate one hour.
Serve.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions crosswise into 1/4 inch slices.
Heat lard in frying pan.
In small dish, place milk.
In a small bowl stir flour and salt well.
Dip onion slices into milk, then flour, repeat twice. Cook 3-5 minutes, drain.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix pork
and
ground
beef
in a bowl.
Cook onions in butter and add
it
to the meat.
Beat eggs and stir them in . Add bread crumbs and milk.
Season to taste.	Form into small balls and fry until golden brown in 10-inch Dutch oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in oven at 325°.
Cool.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown the bacon and chopped onion; add the ground beef and cook until pink color in beef is gone.
Add the cans of beans; season with the salt and mustard, which has been dissolved in the vinegar.
Add the ketchup and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish; bake for 3/4 hour in a 350° oven.
Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken breasts on board and flatten.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs.
Heat oil in large pan and brown chicken on both sides.
Put in shallow baking pan.
Stir rest of ingredients into frying pan and heat. Simmer; put butter in last.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Can now be placed in refrigerator overnight.)
Place Jack cheese on it and bake 10 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Mix sugar, pudding and milk until smooth; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/3 of the graham crackers in pan; add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Layer another 1/3 of graham crackers on top and then a layer of remaining pudding mixture on top of that.
Layer the remaining graham crackers on top and cover with frosting.

title: spinach souffle quiche
directions: You will need 1 (9-inch) glass pie plate, lined with pastry.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and remove to graham cracker crust. Freeze and serve.

title: mixed vegetable pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; bring to boil.
Add vegetables; cook for 5 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Cover with brine and seal.

title: chicken with cream soup marinade
directions: Place the chicken in a baking dish covering each piece with Swiss cheese.
In a bowl, mix one can of soup with the wine and pour over the chicken.
Cover the top of the dish with croutons and bake for 1 hour or until chicken is done at 350°.

title: quick and easy pigs in the blanket
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Chop cabbage into medium pieces and spread in the bottom of the baking dish. Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, breaking up the beef into small pieces.
Stir in rice and pepper.
Drain grease from skillet.
Spoon mixture over the cabbage in a small saucepan; heat the tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip nut bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, water, eggs, butter and brown sugar and mix thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured jelly-roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°; cool.
Frost with a can of vanilla or chocolate frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges.
Dissolve jello and sugar in water.
Chill until partially set.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Keeps for weeks; gets better with age.

title: applesauce cookies with chocolate chips
directions: Ingredients should be at room temperature.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together in large bowl; mix and set aside.
In small bowl, mix the milk and applesauce.
Add egg, sugar, shortening, salt and spices; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in rolled oats and chocolate chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 375°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen small cookies.

title: crisscross cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and beat until mixture is fluffy.
Mix in flour, salt and vanilla and blend well.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Put nuts on large cookie sheet (with sides).
Warm 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and salt gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Pour nuts into egg white mix until coated.
Melt butter in same cookie sheet.
Put nuts on melted butter.
Place in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes to prevent sticking together.

title: homemade bread and buns
directions: Knead together at least 5 minutes.
Let double in size and knead again.
Let rise.
Knead and shape into rolls and bread. Let rise, then bake at 325° for about 30 minutes for buns, 40 minutes for loaves.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix other ingredients together and spread over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large saucepan, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered for 25 minutes.
Add the broccoli to the saucepan and boil for 20 minutes, covered.
Using food processor or blender, whirl the mixture 2 cupfuls at a time until smooth.
Return mixture to saucepan, combine with the cream and bring soup to serving temperature.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
May be served with croutons and/or grated Cheddar cheese.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour; beat well.
Add the softened yeast; mix.
Add enough flour to make dough medium stiff.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (8 to 10 minutes).
Shape in a ball; place in lightly greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface. Cover; let rise until double in size (1 1/4 hours).
Punch down. Cut in 2 portions.
Shape each into smooth ball; cover; let rise 10 minutes.
Shape in loaves; place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans, covered.
Let rise until doubled (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: festive fajitas
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Saute chicken in oil in large skillet, 4 minutes.
Add green pepper and onion; mix lightly. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until Velveeta cubes melt. Fill each tortilla with 1/4
of chicken mixture.
Top with tomatoes, fold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Line bottom and sides of 8-inch pan with aluminum foil and butter it.
Combine all ingredients in a 10-inch skillet.
Bring to a boil over medium heat while stirring.
Boil and stir until golden brown, 5 or 6 minutes.
Spread into buttered pan and cool for 15 minutes.
Peel off foil and break up into pieces.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix ingredients except tomatoes.
Layer tomatoes on bottom of pie crust, spoon mixture over tomatoes.
Bake at 350°
until bubbly.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Bake an angel food cake.
Use tube pan.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Take 3 bowls.
When cake is done and cool, tear in small pieces and place in the three bowls evenly.

title: thelma's bean salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces into large bowl.
Chop tomatoes, cucumbers, onion and green pepper; add to lettuce.
Pour in the drained beans.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: cherry vanilla parfaits
directions: Melt oleo in small skillet over low heat; add pecans.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla wafers and cinnamon; set aside.

title: date krispies
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, dates and salt in a heavy iron or aluminum pan or skillet on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts. Stir until well coated.
Cool to touch and roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in coconut.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: zucchini with tomatoes(zucchini con pomodori)
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan.
Add the onion and garlic; cook until very transparent.
Add cut zucchini and saute for a few minutes.
Add
tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook
on
medium
heat
until lightly tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on for 1/2 hour.
Peel and dice while warm.
Sprinkle with onions (just a few).
Salt and pepper lightly each layer of potatoes, until potatoes are used.
Sprinkle the onions in layers also.
Let potatoes stand for 2 or 3 hours.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fluffy lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve soft drink mix in condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix 2 boxes of Jell-O with package of coconut.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Roll balls into third box of Jell-O.
Different flavors of Jell-O can be used for different colors.

title: beet salad
directions: Dice the beets.
Mince onion.
Chop sardines fine.
Combine with beets and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over.
Serve with chopped parsley generously on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat and onion together, drain grease.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, ground meat, onion and taco seasoning together.
Just before serving, add Doritos and Catalina dressing.

title: taco dip
directions: Can use any vegetable really.

title: volcano cake
directions: In 2 (9 x 9-inch) or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan, sprinkle coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Spread over nuts and coconut. Mix together butter and cream cheese.
Drop from spoon over unbaked cake.
Bake as directed on mix package until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Blend soup, soup mix, sour cream and soup can 1/2 full of milk.
Pour over vegetables and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with Rice Krispies and bake 15 minutes more.

title: white chili
directions: In a large nonstick skillet or saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon oil and saute onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Take care not to burn the vegetables. Remove vegetables and set aside.

title: philadelphia cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Cut beef in thin strips with scissors.
Mix all ingredients except nut.
Lay on wax paper and form into a ball.
Sprinkle ball with nuts and wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add the chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Place golf ball size cookies 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
(Dough is stiff; roll balls of dough rather than drop from spoon. Flatten balls slightly before baking for bigger, flatter cookies.) Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
They should still be a little soft.
Makes 112 to 125 cookies.

title: four day pickles
directions: First Day:
Slice cukes in a gallon jar. Cover with water and 1 cup salt.
Let set 24 hours.

title: aunt montez's cracker thing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Cover cookie sheet with 1 layer of crackers.
Combine margarine and sugar.
Heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers.
Spread chocolate chips over crackers.
Place in oven to melt chips.
Remove from oven.
Spread chocolate over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Allow to cool.

title: southwestern chicken salad spirals
directions: Drain roasted peppers well, pressing between layers of paper towel; chop.
Stir together roasted peppers, chicken, and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Spoon evenly over tortillas, and roll up.
Cut each roll into 5 slices, securing with wooden picks, if necessary.
Yield 40 appetizers.

title: lentil soup
directions: In 4-quart pan, cook onion, celery and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, lentils, barley, bouillon and spices.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with cheese on top.
Great with French bread!

title: canned dried apples
directions: Pour sugar and vinegar over apples in a 1-gallon jar.
Let set overnight.
Next day cook until thick.
Put into jars and seal.

title: firehouse grill sauce(poultry or pork)
directions: Combine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Watch closely as it foams easily.
Brush on after turning each time until 10 minutes prior to being done.
Do not take off grill until outside becomes crispy.

title: low-fat apple walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let fruit juice concentrate thaw to a slushy consistency.
In a medium bowl, sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and allspice.
Set aside.

title: batter-shrimp and oyster
directions: Mix all ingredients together with enough water to make a very soft batter.

title: ozark pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese and sausage souffle(overnighter)
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cool.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Fold in bread, cheese and sausage.
Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Put paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, uncovered.
Remove.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: meat loaf(serves 50)
directions: Mix ground veal, pork and beef together.
Add chopped onion, grated carrots, seasonings, slightly beaten eggs, bread crumbs and milk.
Pack firmly into greased loaf pans, filling them 3/4 full. Three loaf pans about 12 x 4-inches will be needed.
Place slices of bacon or salt pork over the top of the loaf.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 1 hour.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and onion together.
Drain.
Add meat.
Drain again. Mix with other ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with cubed hash brown potatoes, soup, sour cream and chopped green onions (tops and bottoms).
Add cubed cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done. Take breasts out to cool. Put Doritos in chicken broth. Layer Doritos in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut chicken into small amounts and layer on top of Doritos, then add bell pepper and celery, then add cream of chicken soup. Add Ro-Tel. Grate Velveeta cheese, then add to top. Take 2 handfuls of Doritos and crumble on top.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Combine oleo, 1 egg and cake mix.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass, greased cake pan. Cream together cream cheese, brown sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add
eggs.
Blend well.
Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: small orange muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Alternate adding beaten eggs, then the mix of vanilla-buttermilk-soda-juice of 1 orange.
Grind raisins, nuts (I use pecans) and orange peel.
Mix in 1/2 cup flour and add to the first mixture.
Cook in greased and floured tiny muffin tins.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza from scratch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 12-inch
pizza	pan
or cookie sheet.
With greased fingers, press dough into prepared pan, making a 12-inch round and pinching up edges to form rim. With fork,
prick crust several times.
Bake
minutes
or until crust just begins to brown.
Spread
sauce	evenly	over crust. Sprinkle with half of the Mozzarella and
half
of the Parmesan cheese.
Top with sausage,	olives,
mushrooms, green pepper and pepperoni.	Sprinkle with
remaining
cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, using enough mayonnaise to hold it all together.
Serve
with
an assortment of crackers.

title: cherry salad
directions: Put cherry pie filling in bowl; drain pineapple and add the pineapple and Eagle Brand milk into the pie filling.
Place in refrigerator a few hours.
Add Cool Whip when you are ready to serve.
Stir well.
Very rich!

title: all in one casserole
directions: Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper together and set aside.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Spread rice on bottom.
Add 1/3 of flour mixture.
Put in layer of meat; add 1/3 of flour mixture. Add layer of tomatoes.
Add rest of flour mixture.
Spread corn on top.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in boiling water.	Pour over dates and nuts.
Let stand in separate bowl.

title: old fashion ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until lightly colored.
Add sugar, salt and dry gelatin gradually.
Continue beating until thick and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Heat half and half cream and milk to luke warm.
Add to egg mixture and mix; let stand for 15 minutes and pour into freezer can.
Freeze according to your freezer directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla wafers (crushed).
Add pecans.
Bake in a tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: spice cake in a jar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce, water and eggs. Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients in another bowl and add to first mixture.
Add nuts or raisins if desired.
Spray wide mouth pint jars with vegetable spray and fill about 1/2 full.
This will fill 6 - 8 jars.
Bake at 325 degrees exactly 45 minutes.
Remove jars one at a time.
Clean rim of jar and quickly screw the lid on each jar.
Let set until ready to eat.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grind 1 head cabbage and add 1/2 cup sugar; let stand.
Bring to boil remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage and sugar; chill.
Keeps for days.

title: best chocolate cake
