directions: Mix all together well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick delicious rolls
directions: Mix first four ingredients; let stand 20 to 30 minutes in warm place.
Add last four ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Knead on floured board with enough flour to remove stickiness and hold bread together.
Pat or roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pans and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: orange dessert
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients all together with a little water until mixture is smooth.
Add the cold water and bring to a boil, stirring often.
Let cool and add oranges and whipped cream, when ready to serve.

title: indonesian rotti kukus(steamed cake)
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until really creamy.
Add flour slowly, vanilla extract and water with vinegar.
Line colander with wax paper and fill with cake mix.
Put colander on tight fitting pan filled with boiling water.
Cover top of colander, leaving room for the cake to rise.
Steam for 1 hour.
Do not open lid until time is up.
The cake should rise and open up like a flower.

title: cold pizza
directions: Cover slightly greased cookie sheet with crescent rolls.
Bake according to directions.

title: delicious salad
directions: Let pineapple and juice boil 5 minutes.
Pour in jello; cook 2 minutes longer; let cool.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip and nuts.
Let stand overnight.

title: tortilla hors d'oeuvres
directions: In large bowl, combine cheese, olives, chilies and onions. Mix well.
Spread 1/3 cup of cheese mixture to within 1/4 inch of the edge of each tortilla.
Roll tightly, chill until serving (2 hours).
Cut into 8 pieces.
Ends may be trimmed if they look bad. Dip into salsa if desired.

title: sandwich dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in glass jar.
Let stand overnight to develop flavors.
Make hero sandwiches with cold cuts and this party pleasing dressing.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix salt and pepper with hamburger, press on bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Pour soup mixed with water over meat. Top with cheese slices, then tater tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbeque potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done;
drain.
Add salt and pepper. Put potatoes in a casserole dish and pour barbecue sauce over them (add
more sauce, if desired).
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: marinate sauce
directions: Marinate chuck roast or steak for at least 4 hours at room temperature.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and pepper in a saucepan.
Add sweetener and pour over vegetables.
Let marinate for several hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: korean b.b.q.
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip each piece of meat in the sauce and layer in a flat dish or pan.
Pour more marinade on top. Marinate 4 hours before grilling over coals or broiling.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add Fritos and salad dressing last.

title: peach honey dessert
directions: Thaw frozen waffles.
Bake in oven as directed on package. While hot, top with 1 scoop ice cream and spoon on Peach Honey Syrup.

title: pollo alla parmigiana(chicken parmesan)
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Beat egg and water in a shallow bowl. In another bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup grated cheese, salt, pepper and oregano.
Dip chicken in egg, then in flour and cheese mixture.
Put chicken in a 2 1/2-quart casserole and pour melted butter over it.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 45 minutes, brushing occasionally with butter.
Before serving, sprinkle with remaining grated Parmesan cheese.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and Karo until soft ball stage.
Stir constantly.
Remove from stove and add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until ready to pour into buttered pan.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix well the first 8 ingredients with 1/4 cup tomato paste. Put 1/2 cup of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf. Roll or fold cabbage leaf around the meat mixture. Place in baking dish or can cook in crock-pot. Pour remaining tomato paste over top with the basil. Add about 1/2 cup water to the paste. Cook, covered, in oven about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, water and cinnamon to a boil and simmer approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour this mixture over the beets.
Let the beets marinate in this mixture for several hours before serving.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Rinse chilies in cold water.
Split and remove seeds and veins. Layer half in bottom of a 9-inch square casserole dish. Sprinkle Jack cheese on top of chilies. Layer remaining chilies on top. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Beat eggs with flour and then milk. Pour over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour salsa over top of casserole and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christina cookies
directions: If you want, add more, but it is good like it is.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips. Pour cereal in a grocery bag (brown paper).
Pour chocolate chips mixture on Chex. Shake well.
Pour in powdered sugar.
Shake well.
Pour out on cookie sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: green pepper steak(serves 4)
directions: Season your prime rib.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Preheat your gas barbecue to medium heat.
In your conventional barbecue, light your coals.
When they are glowing, move them to the sides and end of the barbecue.
Insert roast meat thermometer so bulk is in the center of the thickest part (being sure it does not rest in fat or bone).
Place your preseasoned prime rib, bone side down, on the grill.
Close lid on barbecue.
Roast for desired degrees of doneness.
The meat thermometer will register:
150° for rare, 160° for medium, 170° for well done.
Allow 19 to 22 minutes per pound for rare, 21 to 24 minutes per pound for medium, and 23 to 26 minutes per pound for well done.
Note:
As with all foods cooked on the barbecue, pay close attention as fat will tend to flame.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion.
Brown meat and drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, beans, chili, garlic powder, ketchup and salt and pepper to taste. Add 1 to 2 tomato cans of water.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add more tomato sauce and water, depending on consistency of chili as it simmers.
Add additional 1/4 cup of ketchup to deepen red color of chili.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grease dish and spread cabbage in bottom of dish. Cook ground beef. Mix cooked meat, onions and rice. Spread over cabbage. Mix soup and water and pour over mixture. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bev's easy refrigerator pickles
directions: In a glass or crockery bowl, alternate layers of cucumbers and onions.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seeds and turmeric.
Bring to a boil, stirring just until sugar dissolves.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Cool slightly.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Store up to one month.
Makes 7 cups.

title: punkin's muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next 6 ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Fill muffin pans, each cup 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pink party salad
directions: Blend the Cool Whip and milk; chill for 1 hour.
Mix together and put into greased dish. Slice into squares.
Can be served as a dessert or a salad after overnight refrigeration.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: finnish flat bread
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk and mix just until dough is moistened.
Knead on floured board for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pat onto an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into pieces.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Reduce speed to low and mix one minute.
Pour batter into 3 prepared pans.
Bake a 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from pans after 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar with spoon until dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Add chopped apples, nuts and coconut; batter will be thick.
Don't use mixer.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: potato pot
directions: Cook potatoes with skins; after potatoes are cooked, not too soft, peel them and cube.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, salt, pepper and onions.
Add potatoes. Mix lightly; pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 teaspoons butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown. Delicious!

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially cook potatoes in boiling water.
Cool.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise.
Place into buttered baking dish large enough for one layer, not packing too closely.
Mix syrup, salt and butter; heat.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, basting often.
If you cut this recipe in half, it makes a pie plate full.

title: deluxe brownies
directions: Make one day before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In a very large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended. Store in a gallon size jar that is airtight.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup water.
Heat to desired temperature; add marshmallows, if desired.
Yummy.

title: potato and cheddar soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large pan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, keeping liquid.
Measure 1 cup; add water if necessary.	Melt butter in pan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until tender but not brown.
Add flour and season.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Gradually add potatoes, liquid, milk and sugar to onion mixture.
Stir well.	Add cheese and ham.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 12 servings.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper, egg, onion, and bread crumbs in bowl and mix.
Form into 1 in. meatballs and brown in hot oil in skillet.
Remove meatballs after browned, drain, and place in 2 qt. casserole.
Blend flour with tomatoes, water, 1/2 tsp. salt, sugar, and basil, stir well.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, and onion.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Pour over meatballs in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, syrup and oatmeal together.
Pat into cookie sheet (jelly roll pan) and bake for 12 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake!
While it is baking, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Spread on cookie mixture and cut while warm.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Grease large container with oil to put dough in.
Turn dough over so dough will have oil on all sides.
Cover container lightly with aluminum foil.
Let stand overnight at room temperature.

title: vegetable tuna salad
directions: Combine flaked tuna, vegetables, chopped eggs and macaroni. Blend Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Toss lightly with tuna mixture.
Use more salad dressing, if necessary.
Chill thoroughly.

title: lemon bars
directions: Bake in 350°
oven for about 15 minutes longer, or just dry on top.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars. Makes about 50 bars.

title: ground turkey pie
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add drained green beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add milk and egg.
Spoon in mounds over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake in hot 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat through.
Serves 8.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, saute onion and bacon until bacon is almost done and onions are clear.
Add potatoes.
Stir coating potatoes on grease.
Add water to just cover potatoes.
Boil until potatoes are done.
Add corns and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream apple squares(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: *Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased 9x9 pan. Bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes. You can also microwave on high 5-6 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix together well and put in dish to set.

title: salted peanut rolls
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except for the marshmallows.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool mixture sufficiently to allow marshmallows to be mixed in without melting.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (with your hands or the back of a spoon) and cut into squares.

title: cinnamon swirl salad
directions: Dissolve candies in boiling water.
Dissolve gelatin in candy liquid.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Cool until partially set.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Spoon over salad. Swirl to marble.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 9 squares.

title: harvey's helper
directions: Hop in car and proceed to nearest grocery store.
Preheat purse by installing checks or cash.
Choose grocery cart that has 4 wheels that work.
Shop until you drop!
Bring home cookies, a cake or even dinner.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
In large skillet, melt butter and brown chicken on both sides (about 10 minutes).
In a small bowl, combine marmalade, lemon juice, cornstarch and dry mustard.
Fold in mandarin oranges.
Carefully fold in grapes.
Pour sauce over chicken and simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until chicken is very tender.

title: pork medallions with sauteed apples
directions: Flatten pork slices with meat mallet, rolling pin or skillet to thickness of 1/8 inch.
Combine breadcrumbs and Parmesan.
Pat pork dry.
Dredge in flour, shaking off excess.
Dip in egg.
Coat with breadcrumb mixture.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Add pork (in batches, if necessary) and cook until light brown, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer to serving platter using slotted utensil.
Keep warm. Makes 4 servings.

title: kindergarten spaghetti
directions: Get tomatoes and meat, then you make the sauce.
Boil the spaghetti.
Then you eat it.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Combine pie filling, gelatin, sugar and water in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Add lime rind and juice. Pour into a bowl and cover with plastic. Chill until cold and slightly thickened.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and freeze or chill.
Top with remaining Cool Whip before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and saute onion in butter.
Boil broccoli and drain. Mix all layers together (broccoli, rice, onion, cream of chicken soup, then cheese; repeat).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: largo seashells
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add macaroni; season with salt.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon celery dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Add oil slowly, constantly beating until thickened. Store in glass container.
Makes 2 quarts.
Keeps 5 to 6 months.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine jello and marshmallows.
Add boiling water and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Have cream cheese softened to room temperature.
Add pineapple and lemon juice. Mix and refrigerate until partially set.
Remove and stir in whipped cream and nuts. Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Make recipe same as for cornbread.
Mix ingredients with cornbread batter and bake at 400°.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over cake mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: harvest vegetable scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine carrots, broccoli and 1/2 can of onion rings with potatoes.
Dot vegetables evenly with cheese.
Pour milk over vegetables; sprinkle with seasonings as desired.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Add pudding and Cool Whip to right consistency.
Don't use any of the juice.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain dry lima beans, green baby lima beans and kidney beans. Add to baked beans.
Remove fried bacon and add onion to bacon drippings, saute.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and garlic powder.
Mix all together well.
Add to bean mixture in large pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: olive loaf
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Shape 1/3 of mixture into flat loaf shape in baking pan.
Center 6 olives down loaf.
Top with another 1/3 mixture.
Place two lines of olives down outer sides of loaf.
Top with remaining mixer and pat firmly.
Weave bacon over top of loaf, sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in order given, adding one egg at a time.
Beat well.
Bake in two (8 x 5-inch) loaf pans (greased and floured) at 350° for 40 minutes.
Before removing from pans, mix the rest of ingredients and pour over loaves.
Let set 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.

title: yogurt-dill dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a small bowl; mix until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate the unused portion in an airtight container; use it within 2 days.

title: connie's gingersnaps
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the first mixture and mix well.
Roll into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° until cracked on top, about 8 to 9 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello and 1/3 cup sugar in hot water, then add marshmallows.
Sit in refrigerator.
When it starts to sit, stir in the drained pineapple and 3 bananas.
Put in long, flat dish to jell.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook 1 cup diced peaches, water, sugar and cornstarch until clear and thick; let cool.
Have ready a 9-inch baked pie shell. Dice 3 cups of peaches into pie shell.
Top with cooked peaches and serve with whipped cream.
Make 2 hours before serving.

title: kid's lunch pizzas(microwave)
directions: Toast oe medium toaster setting one English muffin (split). Top each half with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce and 1 tablespoon each of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Put a paper towel on a paper plate and put the muffin half on the paper towel.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100%) for 30 to 45 seconds, until cheese is melted.
Cool about 2 minutes before eating.
Makes 1 serving.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Chop cookies and then add slightly melted butter.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Chill until stiff.
Place ice cream on top.
You may use vanilla or any other flavor you prefer.
Frozen yogurt may also be substituted.
Place in freezer and prepare topping.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into large mixing bowl. Combine 1 stick of margarine, 4 teaspoons cocoa, shortening and water.
Bring to a rapid boil. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ginny's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Mix fruit and nuts with 3/4 cup flour. Sift remaining 1 cup flour and baking powder.
Fold into egg and butter mixture. Add flavoring.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Grease and line tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours (or until toothpick tests clean).

title: english yorkshire pudding
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until crumbly.
Add milk and eggs.
Beat at high with mixer for 5 to 7 minutes.
Chill. Heat muffin tins or individual ramekins in oven; spray well with Pam and fill 1/3 to 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with syrup or cooked fruit.

title: cream cheese nut ball
directions: Mix all ingredients,
except
the
pecans, together and form into a ball.
Roll
the
ball
in the ground pecans.
Top with a cherry and refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: country ham with red-eye gravy
directions: Fry ham slices slowly in frying pan on low heat until cooked to desired tenderness. Remove ham from pan. (Leave drippings.) Add water slowly to ham drippings. Bring to rapid boil. Pour gravy into heat resistant bowl. Serve gravy over ham or with rice or grits.

title: soybean chili
directions: An economical way of using bacon and eggs left from a previous meal is to put them in a wooden bowl and chop them quite fine, adding a little mashed or cold chopped potato and a little brown gravy, if any was left.
Mix and mold it into little balls.
Roll in raw egg and cracker crumbs and fry it in a spider the same as frying eggs.
Fry a light brown on both sides.
Serve hot.
Very appetizing.

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown beef; drain off fat.
Combine all but onions; mix well.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.
Cover top with onions.
Put in oven for 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, and eggs thoroughly.
Blend in flour.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With a fork, flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: austrian sausage and sauerkraut soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 5 hours or until vegetables are tender.
If necessary, skim off fat before serving.
May cook in crock-pot 10 to 12 hours.
Excellent hearty soup for cold days.

title: glorified riceburgers
directions: Combine meat, onion, salt, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Shape into 4 patties. Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown on one side. Turn and broil other side 4 or 5 minutes or until brown. Top each patty with 1/4 cup cooked rice. Sprinkle with cheese. Return to broiler until cheese melts. Spoon drippings over.
Serves 4.

title: oyster tomatoes
directions: Remove stems from cherry tomatoes.
Slit the center of each tomato.
Insert one smoked oyster into each tomato.

title: german chocolate cake(uncommonly good; 3-layer)
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool. Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and chocolate. Set aside. Mix flour, soda and salt. Beat chocolate mixture into flour alternately with buttermilk. Beat in sour cream. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into batter. Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans, lined on the bottoms with waxed and greased paper; grease and flour sides of pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 15 minutes in pan; remove and cool on racks. Spread coconut pecan filling between layers and chocolate or white frosting on top and sides.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and oleo with a fork.
Make hole in the middle of dry and oleo.

Put milk and eggs in hole to beat, then mix all together. Roll out on floured surface, folding in half. Repeat rolling and folding (the more you roll and fold, the flakier they will be, within reason).
Bake at 350° to 400° for 6 to 8 minutes on ungreased sheet.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed and pour over the coconut and nuts.
Combine cream cheese and margarine with powdered sugar.
Blend this and drop by spoonfuls onto the cake.
Don't swirl.
Bake for 45 minutes.
When you serve, flip the cake pieces over so the nuts and coconut are on top.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix thoroughly; serve chilled. Good and inexpensive.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions on package.
Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Over low heat, saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef and salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Let it get good and hot, then add sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour and beat well.
Melt margarine and add to mixture.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain.
Add the next 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove the bay leaf.
Serve over spaghetti.
Yields 4 to 6 servings (about 1 quart).

title: fresh homemade salsa
directions: Bring tomatoes to a simmer in a saucepan with vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour or longer for a thicker consistency.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak dried apricots for 20 minutes.
Cream together 1 cup of sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well; drain apricots.
Add with nuts to batter.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 65 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
This bread keeps well.

title: regina cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl; cut in the shortening.
When blended, add the eggs, one at a time, mixing to a soft dough.

title: pear chips
directions: Add sugar and ginger to cut up pears.
Let stand overnight. Add lemon, cut into small pieces.
Cook slowly 3 hours.
Seal in hot jars.
Cook 5 minutes at 7 pounds of pressure.

title: egg strata(quiche)
directions: Butter bread and cube; set aside.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Add bread; stir well.
Bake in buttered 9-inch pie pan or 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: no fried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking sheet.
Mix egg whites with spice.
Coat potatoes; place in baking sheet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until fries are crispy, turning every 8 to 10 minutes to brown them evenly.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Small
cucumbers
are best for bread and butter pickles. To prepare
them,
first
wash,
then
slice very thin without peeling and soak with onions for 2 hours in cold water in which salt
has been dissolved.
Drain well.
Heat remaining ingredients until they boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and cook until transparent.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add sugar, flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add tomato juice and drained beans. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours; stir occasionally.

title: cheese bread
directions: Spread on cookie sheet 1 package crescent rolls.
Blend by hand cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and egg yolk (save egg white).
Pour mixture over crescent rolls.
Use second package of crescent rolls to cover mixture.
Brush egg white (unbeaten) over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately after removing from oven, sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.

title: dark sweet fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of pan.
In large bowl, combine egg and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand; stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° as directed for pan sizes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender or food processor, process oats until coarse flour.
In small bowl, combine ground oats, flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In large mixing bowl with electric mixer on high, beat butter and brown sugar until light and creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well combined. Gradually stir in flour mixture until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.

title: nut oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar together.
Add egg and milk and stir all together.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add oats, nuts and raisins (if desired).
Mix well.

title: everready muffins
directions: Combine bran, sugar, flour, soda, spice and salt in very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well. Store in refrigerator in covered container up to 6 weeks.
When ready to bake, fill greased muffin tins or paper cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot and spicy dip
directions: Take Ro-Tel tomatoes and chop into small pieces. Mix the soups and sour cream together.
Then add the chopped tomatoes.
Stir all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Great with king size corn chips.

title: microwave rotel chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Saute onion and bell pepper.
Cook spaghetti.
In microwave dish, combine cheese, soup, Ro-Tel and mushrooms.
Heat until soupy.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Heat through and through in oven or microwave.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 400° until rim of crust begins to brown slightly. Decrease heat to 300° for 45 minutes, until filling is set.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sweetener and peanut butter in bowl.
Mix in egg, milk and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Drop by spoonful on foil-lined baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix together, then bake at 250° until bubbly.

title: red leaf salad
directions: Mix Good Seasons almost according to directions: Use olive oil (I use 3/4 olive oil and 1/4 regular oil). No water. Add extra garlic powder.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together; pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Brush with butter and bake 10 minutes.

title: white cloud frosting(very easy)
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar, continuously beating until soft peaks form.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Cut artichoke hearts into small pieces, then mash with a fork. (Do not puree in blender.)
Add breadcrumbs, eggs and cheese. Heat olive oil until very hot.
Remove from heat.
Add garlic and wait until garlic stops sizzling.
Pour oil and garlic into artichoke mixture.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator overnight or at least one hour.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls into mixture of 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs and 1 tablespoon cheese; mix more as needed.
Yield:
50 balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Eat cool or warm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put cereal in a very large bowl. Mix dry ingredients and mix well with cereal. Mix eggs, buttermilk and oil together and pour over cereal, mixing well. Add nuts, if you like. Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: sweet herb sorbet
directions: Place the sugar in a saucepan and add the water.
Bring to the boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved.
Chop[ the herb leaves and add to the pan.
Cover, then remove from the heat.
Leave to infuse for 20 to 30 minutes.
Test for flavor, if it is too light, bring to the boil again then leave to infuse for 15 minutes. Strain the liquid and add the lemon juice.
Transfer the mixture to an ice cube tray and freeze for 2 to 3 hours.
When the sorbet is semi-frozen, whisk the egg white until stiff and fold it into the mixture.
Return to the freezer for a further 3 to 4 hours or until frozen.
Serve the sorbet in individual dishes and decorate each serving with extra herb leaves.
Serves 4.

title: black devil's food cake(heart association)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Add the oil and buttermilk. Stir until well blended. Bring the coffee to a boil and stir it gently into the batter.
Mixture will be soupy. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: watermelon salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let it congeal slightly.
Mix in melon, pineapple and nuts.
Let congeal until firm.

title: wesson oil stir-n-roll pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Pour oil and milk together in measuring cup.
Pour liquid into flour mixture.
Stir with fork until flour is moistened.
Divide dough into 2 pieces and roll each half between 2 pieces of waxed paper.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spread coconut on bottom of pan. Spread nuts on top of coconut. Prepare cake mix as directed. Pour over coconut and nuts. Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine together until blended (not thin). Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls on top of batter, but away from edge of pan. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy lemon cream salad dressing for fruit(1927)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Add grated orange rind and juice of orange and lemon.
Add boiling water.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and add 1/2 pint of whipped cream before serving.
If not using double boiler, be careful and stir.

title: sugar crumb cookies
directions: Sift flour in a large bowl. Add shortening until coarse like meal. Stir in sugar. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Mix in milk and vanilla. Stir until well blended and chill for several hours. Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: to die for banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bananas, vanilla wafers and pecans.
Place thin layer of mixture on bottom of glass dish. Add layer of vanilla wafers and bananas, then add mixture and repeat the process of layering.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish, 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cook, uncovered; if gets too brown, cover.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and butter together until onions are tender. Add sugar and continue cooking until onions turn light brown.
At the same time, boil water and bouillon cubes.
Add onions and simmer 30 minutes.	Serve in bowl topped with toasted bread, Mozzarella cheese and a sprinkle of Parmesan.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: chicken and red peppers
directions: Deep-fry (or bake) chicken wings; drain and apply hot sauce. Use butter mixed with hot sauce to determine desired taste.

title: frozen cranberry slush
directions: In a Confederate camp, somewhere in Virginia.
"The night was excessively cold and we passed the evening in toasting our toes before a roaring fire, talking of home and the dear ones there in anything but a joyous strain.
We had made up our mind to go egg-nogless to bed when, about 11 o'clock, the welcome sound of horses hoofs on the crisp snow outside.
Out we rushed and there we found the tardy Mose with his well-filled demijohn.

The eggs were quickly beaten, the sugar stirred in, the whiskey added, and we had one of the most delicious nogs that ever a mortal man quaffed. Taking a couple of glasses apiece, we retired merrily to bed, to forget the hardships of a soldier's life and dream of a joyful reunion with the dear absent ones so far away."

title: festive cooked carrots
directions: Mix cornstarch or flour with pineapple juice and cinnamon to make paste.
Cook until thick.

title: swedish cardamon coffee cake
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Add enough flour to make a thick batter; beat until smooth.
Add yeast mixture and eggs; beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar, egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, chocolate chips and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sherry sponge cake
directions: In food processor or blender, whirl almonds until finely ground.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon into large bowl; stir in ground almonds until well mixed, set mixture aside.

title: easy sugar cut-out cookies
directions: Mix butter and both sugars until smooth.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Roll dough into ball; put in refrigerator overnight in airtight container.
Using floured rolling pin, roll dough out on floured surface.
Roll into 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into shapes with cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool and decorate.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: orange cream cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg yolk and orange rind in small mixer bowl at high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Add flour to butter mixture; beat at medium speed just until thoroughly mixed.
Shape dough into ball; refrigerate wrapped in plastic wrap 1 hour.

title: bernie's chili
directions: Brown hamburger, drain grease.
Saute in the onion, garlic and pepper until tender.
Throw in all other ingredients.
Simmer for at least 2 hours (stirring pretty often) until carrots and potatoes are tender.

title: marinated artichoke hearts and mushrooms
directions: Clean and quarter mushrooms.
Drain artichokes. Whisk mustard, vinegar, oil, garlic and basil together.
Marinate mushrooms and half of peppers in vinaigrette.
Marinate artichokes with remaining peppers and vinaigrette.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Fry
onions and hamburger until hamburger is done.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms and soup and cook over low heat about 1 hour.
Cook
spaghetti
in
salted
water.
Cover
with grated cheese.

title: spinach dip
directions: *I let the spinach thaw, then I squeeze all the liquid out of the spinach I can.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix apricots and juice in blender; mix together other ingredients and add apricots.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
While cake is hot, turn pan upside down.
Melt apricot preserves and drizzle over warm cake.

title: wilted spinach salad a l'orange
directions: Tear spinach and set to side.
Cook bacon until crispy (save grease).
Crumble bacon into bits. On medium-low temperature, add vinegar, sugar, lemon juice and juice from mandarin oranges to bacon grease.

title: holiday magic yams
directions: Drain peaches; reserve juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup peach juice; set aside.
In 11-inch skillet heat remaining juice, brown sugar, cranberry sauce, cinnamon and butter.
When butter melts, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until it thickens.
Add potatoes.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in peaches.
Cook additional 5 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, parsley flakes, salt and pepper. Stir in potatoes, celery and onions. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: pumpernickel spinach dip
directions: Defrost the spinach and remove excess water.
In a large bowl combine onions, spinach and soup mix with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Cut off top of round bread loaf and hollow out, reserving bread taken out.
Fill hollow with dip mixture.
Tear reserved bread into large bite size pieces and arrange around filled loaf.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Cream butter with half the sugar.
Beat eggs with other half of sugar in separate bowl.
Combine both mixtures.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk to above sugar/egg/butter mixture.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and tomato soup over low heat until cheese melts.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/8 cup cold water and add to cheese and tomato soup mixture while it is still warm.
Then add rest of the ingredients.
Chill and serve with party rye or Ritz crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour in 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can add 2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
(Ovens vary in heat; may have to cook longer.)

title: cold sesame noodles
directions: Cook noodles in large pot of boiling unsalted water until barely tender and still firm. Drain immediately and rinse with cold water until cool. Drain really well and transfer to wide bowl. Toss with sesame oil so they don't stick. In small saucepan, heat peanut oil over medium-low flame. Add green onions, ginger, garlic and chili paste. Cook and stir for a minute, until soft and fragrant. Mix in the brown sugar, peanut butter, vinegar, soy sauce and hot water. Stir until the sugar is dissolved and the peanut butter has smoothed out. Toss the noodles with the peanut sauce until well coated. Serve at room temperature or chilled. Garnish with the sesame seeds, cucumber slices and cilantro.

title: my mother's apple pirog (pie)
directions: Pare apples, cut into eighths and discard centers with seeds. Cover with 1/2 cup sugar (1 cup if you prefer greater sweetness), cinnamon and oatmeal.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside while preparing the dough.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve the orange sherbet in hot water. Cool and add pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican lunch
directions: Brown sausage, onions and pepper in skillet.
Add tomatoes, sour cream, macaroni and seasoning.
Stir and cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 9-day cole slaw
directions: Grate first 4.
Add next 3.
Bring last 3 to boil and immediately pour over.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
After 24 hours, this may be frozen.
The slaw keeps for weeks.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the sugar, water and white syrup together until spins thread.
Add the peanuts; cook and stir until golden brown.
Have ready the last 3 ingredients; mix and pour onto 2 cookie sheets which have been buttered.
Spread and cool.
Break into pieces.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening or oil.
Add boiling water.
Blend well.
Divide in two.
Can chill, but not necessary. Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Peel off one side and lay dough in pan.
Peel off other side and do what you usually do with pie dough.
Can be kept in fridge up to 2 weeks.
Just add a bit of boiling water and work up like it was before.
Flaky and easy to do.

title: my secret brownie recipe
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar together, then add butter.
Stir until creamy, then add eggs one at a time.
Do not beat mixture.
Add vanilla and rum or liqueur; stir.
Add flour in halves, then stir in nuts.
Pour batter in greased 9 x 9-inch metal pan, not glass. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Brownies should be chewy, not dry.

title: giant crisp chocolate-chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar until light. Beat
in
egg
and
vanilla
until blended and fluffy. Stir in flour
mixture,
nuts and chocolate until well mixed. Shape in 2-inch
balls;
place
inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheets (6
on
each
sheet).
Bake
on
middle rack in preheated 350° oven
for
20 to 23 minutes or until golden and edges are
lightly browned.
Cool completely on cookie sheet. Store covered
in
dry cool
place.
Makes
twenty-one 4-inch cookies.

title: sloppy joe under a bun
directions: In a skillet, cook beef until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in Sloppy Joe sauce; mix well.
Transfer to a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, eggs and milk just until well blended.
Pour over cheese; sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all together well and put into well-buttered 9x13x2-inch pan.

title: easy mix chocolate cake
directions: Put in mixing bowl in given order.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Frost when cool.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Combine milk, margarine and bread; blend.
Add egg, cheese, salt, mushrooms and onion; mix well.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Put all the ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes. Pour over the baked crust. Take the 2nd crust and cut into strips. Lattice over the top of the peach mixture. Sprinkle lightly with sugar. Put in the oven and bake until golden brown.

title: knox blox
directions: In
a large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with flavored gelatin;
add
boiling
water
and	stir until completely dissolved.* Pour into
x
9-inch
baking
pan and chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1 inch squares. Makes 9 dozen blox.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate and serve.

title: pumpkin oat bran muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix bran, flour, wheat flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and ginger.
In another bowl, beat egg whites to blend with milk, oil and pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter equally into 1 dozen paper lined 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until tops are well browned.

title: cheese topped stuffed peppers
directions: In large kettle of boiling water, parboil peppers for 5 minutes and drain.
In a medium skillet, cook beef and onion until browned.
Drain off excess fat; add rice, salt and 1 cup tomato sauce, heating thoroughly.
Heat oven to 350°.
Stuff each pepper with beef mixture and place in ungreased baking dish large enough to contain peppers.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers and cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles.
Spread spaghetti sauce in bottom of bread pan.
Put a layer of noodles.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top of noodles.
Put a layer of pepperoni, a layer of ham, a layer of mushrooms and a layer of cheese.
Repeat until you run out of noodles.

title: oklahoma coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan by cake directions on box. While still warm, punch holes all over cake.
Mix cream of coconut and milk; pour over cake.
When cool, frost with flaked coconut, pecans and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add melted chocolate, instant coffee and rum extract.
Stir in flour and broken walnuts and turn into pie shell.
Top with remaining walnut halves.
(I arrange them around the outer edge of pie filling and a few in the center.)
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Cut in at least 8 pieces, as it is very rich.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, pineapple, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Sift together the soda and flour.
Add this to the first mixture.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 400° for about 8 to 10 or 12 minutes.

title: mary ester's rice
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, melt butter.
Add the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven, then add cheese; leave in oven until cheese is melted.

title: soft cookie
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Add flour to suit; then add nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix to a soft dough for drop cookies or add more flour to suit for rolled cookies.

title: harvest pie filling
directions: Wash raisins and drain.
Cook raisins, apples, brown sugar, salt and orange until apples are tender.
Moisten cornstarch with 1 tablespoon of water and add to the hot fruit.
Stir gently. Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with yogurt or whipped topping.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place over white rice.

title: lo-cal chicken primavera
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken, mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and vegetables become soft.
Add olives and tomatoes that have been broken into chunks.
Add seasonings. Simmer mixture gently to partially reduce liquid.
Serve over a bed of Italian Risotto or pasta of your choice.
Serves 4.

title: good potato salad
directions: Mix oil, lemon juice, sugar, mustard and chicken bouillon together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Marinate for 3 hours or more.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: 500 cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter in large pan (roaster) in 200° oven.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a glass bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave on High for about 6 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook 10 minutes on High.
Remove from oven.
Add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Cool until creamy; drop on waxed paper.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Arrange frog legs in a shallow container. Combine eggs, mayonnaise, cornstarch, lemon juice, baking powder, salt and pepper; stir until smooth. Pour over frog legs. Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes. Combine flour and bread crumbs in a plastic bag. Remove legs from marinade, shaking off excess. Place 2 or 3 legs at a time in flour mixture.
Close bag; shake until legs are well coated. Pour oil 2 to 3 inches deep. Fry legs until dark golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: egg surprise
directions: Use crescent rolls to line pan. Scramble eggs and milk.
Pour over crescent rolls. Fry bacon until crisp.
Put in egg mixture and other ingredients.
Pour cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cavatini(makes one 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water.
Brown hamburger, sausage, onion and pepperoni.
When nearly done, add mushrooms.
Cook until done. Add tomato sauce.
Combine with pasta.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix ground meat and taco seasoning mix with 1/2 cup water; simmer for 15 minutes.
Fry tortillas in hot shortening to soften. Drain.
Fill each with 2 tablespoons beef mixture.
Roll and place, seam side down, in greased shallow baking dish.
In saucepan, heat sour cream and drained green chilies to thin sauce. Cover enchiladas with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Garnish with jalapenos, if desired.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove cover 3 to 5 minutes to brown lightly.
Serves 6.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the bean dip and taco mix. Spread mixture on a 10-inch tray or in a 10-inch pie plate. Blend together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over bean dip. Sprinkle sliced olives over top along with tomatoes and cheese and lettuce.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into deep oven dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together, then pour into dish over butter.
Do not stir. Next, add can of peaches (if peaches are sweet, add less sugar) over mixture again.
Do not stir.
Place in 350° oven and bake until crust is brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions in small amount of oil.
Add other ingredients. Boil until vegetables are done.
You may thicken with mixture of one tablespoon flour and 1/2 cup water.

title: cake frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Work softened butter in.
Add vanilla. Slowly add milk until it reaches spreadable consistency (about 3 tablespoons).

title: wedding cakes
directions: In medium size bowl with mixer, beat butter and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stand on sheet for 2 to 3 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Cool completely, then roll again in sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.
Can be frozen up to 3 months.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs until well blended. Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt, stirring until dough is formed.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Turn out onto lightly floured pastry sheet; roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 min.
Cool on wire racks.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and pudding and mix well.
Drain oranges and pineapple chunks.
Add to Cool Whip along with pecans.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well, cover and chill.

title: cookie crayons
directions: Place liners in muffin pan.
Place peeled crayons in muffin tins.
(You will need at least seven regular crayons.)
Be sure to use a variety of colors.
Place muffin pan in an oven at 250° until crayons melt.
Do not move muffin pan!!!
When crayon melts, turn off oven and when oven is cool, remove muffin pan.
Peel foil and your BIG crayons are ready.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, spices and salt.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to first mixture.
Mix in flour and prunes. Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bill's chili cheese crab dip
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature. Cream mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasoned salt. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and crab meat. Mix thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: jailbreak spice cake
directions: Mix all together and pour in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with Jailbreak frosting.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, salt and spices. Add to mixture alternately with milk in which soda has been dissolved. Add jam and beaten egg whites. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 375°.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in the middle of cake comes out clean.
Makes 3 to 9 layers, depending on amount of batter used per layer.

title: sweet potato corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, saute bacon over medium heat until crisp and brown.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Add onion, red pepper, leek, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper to bacon drippings.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add sweet potato, corn, chicken broth and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook until sweet potatoes are tender (20 minutes).

Mix cornstarch into remaining 1/2 cup water and stir into soup mixture. Heat soup to boiling, stirring constantly and cook until thickened. Reduce heat to low, stir in cream and reserved bacon; heat until bubbles appear.

title: baked apple macaroni
directions: Alternate macaroni and apples in layers in baking dish. Combine cream and sugar and pour over macaroni and apples.
Pour half and half over macaroni and apples until they are covered. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° until tender (about 30 minutes).
This dish can be used for breakfast, lunch or supper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Add onion salt, celery salt and milk.
Mash until no lumps.
Blend in mayonnaise, mustard, olives and eggs.
Blend in dill pickles (using pickle juice only if needed for desired consistency).
Slice one hard-boiled egg and arrange on top.
Serve warm or cold.
Tastes best after it is refrigerated for 24 hours.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix
the
first
5 ingredients thoroughly; shape into a ball. Let
stand	in refrigerator for at least an hour.
Roll over nuts and parsley.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add the powdered sugar, creaming well.
Add the evaporated milk, vanilla, salt and butter flavoring; mix well.
Blend in the flour.
Mix thoroughly.
If necessary, chill for easier handling.
Roll out the dough half at a time on a floured surface to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch circles or squares.
Place the cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Spread a teaspoon of the filling on each.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon of icing on each.
Decorate with a pecan half.

title: pineapple almond date bread
directions: Toast 3/4 cup almonds, save the remaining 1/4 cup for topping. Beat sugar and margarine in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg until blended.
Stir in undrained pineapple and orange peel.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg in a medium bowl.
Beat into pineapple mixture until blended.
Stir in 3/4 cup toasted almonds and dates.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup untoasted almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: trailside treats
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt. Set aside.

title: old fashioned kentucky baked chicken
directions: Mix flour, paprika, dressing and soup.
Shake chicken in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until juice runs clear (not pink).

title: devilish dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with vegetable dippers or potato chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cup serving.

title: brenda's apple crisp
directions: Put apples in dish.
Cover with white sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt, lemon juice, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix oats, 1/2 cup flour, brown sugar and 3/4 cube butter or margarine. Press over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with fresh whipped cream or ice cream.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and whipping cream; mix well.
Add vanilla; mix again.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Delicious!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla together; add potato chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Then add flour and mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet; crush with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Cut off top of bread and hollow out center.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Fill bread and let it sit awhile before serving.
Use bread from top and hollowed out center (that has been cut into serving pieces) to dip.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onions in butter for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream and cook gently for 10 minutes, not allowing mixture to boil.
Serve over rice.

title: beef and chicken casserole
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Boil chicken until done.
Let cool and debone chicken.
Put bacon strips in bottom of casserole dish. Layer half of chicken and half of beef on bacon.
Heat soup and cream cheese together until cheese is melted.
Pour half of soup mixture on top of beef.
Layer other half of chicken and beef and pour rest of soup mixture on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in the sour cream.
In another mixing bowl, sift together the baking powder, soda and flour; cut in shortening.
Pour into the sugar-egg-cream mixture and mix slightly.
Do not overmix.
Pour half the batter into a small, greased tube pan and sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour the remaining batter over the brown sugar, etc.
and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, pimientos and purple onion in a bowl; toss gently. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients. Stir well and pour over pea mixture. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for about 35 minutes or until soft, cool, peel and slice for casserole.
Cream together butter, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, orange rind and orange concentrate (the juice should be partially thawed).
Arrange layers of sweet potato (half) in casserole; cover with 1/2 sugar-butter mixture.
Add the remaining potatoes, top with all butter-sugar mixture.
Place in heated oven at 350° until heated through; remove and sprinkle with chopped pecans and cover with marshmallows; return to oven and brown lightly.
Watch closely as marshmallows burn quickly.

title: jerk sauce(for any meat)
directions: Mix all ingredients (coarsely chopping all vegetables).
Let this whole thing sit for 1 day before using.
Yield is about 1 gallon.

title: tortellini and shrimp salad
directions: Boil tortellini until tender.
Drain and place in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add cottage cheese and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and knead lightly.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and knead.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart round baking dish.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 300° oven until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: congealed salad
directions: In large bowl, mix cottage cheese and orange Jell-O.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Stir.
Add Cool Whip and stir mixture. Refrigerate 4 or 5 hours before serving.

title: chocolate tortilla torte
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate chips, sour cream and powdered sugar together.
Let cool.
Then layer tortillas and chocolate mixture, spreading thinly on tortillas.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Put water and cranberries in heavy pan and cook until they pop. Add the raisins and chopped orange; cook 5 minutes.
Add sugar and cook until thick jelly stage.
Remove from heat.
Add black walnuts.
Serve as side dish when cool or place in jars and seal.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, with baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until fine.
Combine with milk and food coloring.
Add to flour mixture. Stir until moist.
Knead on floured surface 12 times.
Roll to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Combine olives, almonds and reserved meat. Spread over dough.
Roll up starting with a 12-inch side cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place meat mixture in 12 x 8-inch or 11-inch round baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil the chicken breasts in water to cover with the celery and onion. Mix together the soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Cut the chicken into bite size pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Pour soup mix over chicken. Take the crackers and crush. Mix with the melted margarine.
Crumble over top of soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: party cracker mix
directions: Mix oil with dressing and dill weed and pour over crackers. Shake to coat.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350°. Check and stir after 1 hour.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, fill paper cups.
Cream 8 oz. cream cheese, sugar eggs stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 tsp. in each cupcake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15- 20 minutes.
Can frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: microwave vegetable lasagna
directions: Put zucchini in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in mushrooms, cook 5 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
In a bowl, mix egg with cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, the Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Spread about 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce over bottom of baking dish, cover with half of noodles.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs.
Layer with half of zucchini mixture and then half of cheese mixture.
Repeat, spread spaghetti sauce and the 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese over top.
Loosely cover with waxed paper, cook in microwave on High 15 minutes, until heated through.

title: fried corn-cakes
directions: Mix and drop by spoonful into hot greased pan and fry on medium heat until done.
Heat may have to be lowered.
Some pans may stick.
I use a Silverstone coated pan.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except 2 tablespoons onion and red pepper, until well blended.
Spoon into 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onion and red pepper.

title: cheese and spinach soup
directions: Bring broth, spinach and onion to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes (longer if spinach is still frozen). In separate bowl, blend flour and evaporated milk. Pour into broth mixture and cook until thick. Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Dissolve each Jello pkg. in
1 1/2 cups hot water.
Put in separate dishes and let set until very firm.
Dissolve 1 pkg. Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add this to 1 cup hot pineapple juice.
Stir until dissolved. Set aside to cool.

title: glass candy(good for kids to help make.)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Continue boiling without stirring until a drop cracks in cold water.
Wash away crystals with wet cloth; remove from heat.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Set outside on cold day, cool and crack.

title: rabbit stew
directions: Wash
rabbit
and
pat
dry.
Wipe
with
vinegar.
In skillet, saute rabbit and onions in oil with bacon and seasoning. Add chicken
broth and simmer until tender.
Add raisins and chocolate and cook for an additional 11 minutes.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan; bring to boil; boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter, chocolate chips and vanilla; beat 10 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: popular bible cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake slowly at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: light baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with 4 cups water and let stand 2 hours. Drain.
Combine beans and 4 cups water in large pan and simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Fry bacon with onion.
In bean pot or ovenproof dish, combine beans with liquid and rest of ingredients including bacon grease.
Cook and bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350° until beans are tender.
Stir occasionally, adding water if necessary.
Remove cover last 30 minutes to brown; do not stir. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fillet of fish almondine
directions: Microwave 2 minutes. Add almonds. Cook for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cola-cola bing cherry dessert
directions: Drain fruit, reserve juice.
Measure juice using 2 cups. Heat to boiling, dissolve jello.
Use remaining juice and Coca-Cola to 2 Cups.
Add, stir in.
Cool until syrupy.
Cut cherries when gelatin has begun to set.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Mix in cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip with beaters. Spread on set jello.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Mix together crackers, 1/2 cup sugar and chopped nuts.
Fold cracker mixture into egg white mixture.
Bake in a greased pie plate at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Delicious even without frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, adding salt and pepper to taste and 1/2 stick of butter (margarine).

Take all meat from the bones. In a casserole dish, add a layer of chicken, a layer of yellow rice, then a layer of cream of chicken soup, then a layer of chicken and a layer of rice, then a layer of cream of mushroom soup, another layer of chicken, and a last layer of yellow rice. Then add crushed Ritz crackers mixed with 1/2 stick of melted butter as a top layer.
Add some broth to casserole.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: dream squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Press evenly over bottom of pan for crust. Bake 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, rinse in cold water, drain and place in serving bowl.
Add vegetables, feta cheese, pepperoni and oregano.

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix the ground beef, crumbs, 1/4 cup soup, onion, egg and seasonings.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves; brown on both sides in skillet in shortening.
Cover; cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup, water and mustard.
Top loaves with cheese.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine with squash; add bread crumbs, pimento and beaten eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart glass baking dish and sprinkle with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: thunder and lightning
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put about 1/2 water and 1/2 vinegar to cover mixture to top.
You need to taste as you mix sugar, vinegar and red pepper to see how you prefer it.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread cubed toast along bottom of large, lightly greased casserole dish; layer mushrooms, onion and sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk and margarine.
Pour egg mixture over casserole; top with shredded Cheddar and Feta cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Season potatoes with salt and pepper and chill.
Fry in bacon drippings and brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels; coat each side with sugar and serve very hot.

title: conch(modern)
directions: Crush garlic; chop parsley.
In a large pot, place conch, in its shell, into boiling water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at low heat.
Remove conch and place in cold water.
Remove meat from the shell.
Cut off hard outer skin.
Slice meat and cover with a mixture made from remaining ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in the butter flavored Crisco.
It will be really coarse.
This will keep in the refrigerator 4 weeks or longer.
When you are ready to make a pie, take out what you need and add water to make a dough that will roll out.

title: mother's cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except for soda.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir together with dry ingredients.
Heat bacon grease in large iron skillet or heavy pan.
Stir about half of grease into batter, then pour into hot skillet with rest of grease in it. Bake about 25 minutes at 450°.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a slow boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt.
Pour boiling water over meal and stir at the same time.
Add cubes of oleo until melted in corn meal. When cool enough, add 1 egg and beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Beat well.
Oil a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in corn meal mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no-fail chocolate frosting
directions: Stir and cook 1 minute. Take off burner and beat with spoon until not glossy.
Spread on cake or use as candy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sift.
Store in airtight container.
Fill cup half full of mixture and add boiling water. Stir and enjoy.

title: florentine crescents
directions: In saucepan, combine spinach, cheese spread, crumbs and bacon. Stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Unroll dough. Cut crescent rolls in half lengthwise, 32 triangles. Spread each triangle with rounded teaspoonful spinach mixture. Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Brush dough with beaten egg (or just use the whites), if desired. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Drain kidney and butter beans.
Brown ground beef and onions. Drain off fat.
Then add all the beans and seasonings.
Pour into a large casserole and bake 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Cook
potatoes in kettle of boiling water until tender. Drain. Cool enough to peel.
Cut into chunks.
Separate yolks from whites.
Chop
whites
and
add to potatoes with chopped onions and celery.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell to bake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: *Use liquid from fruit and add water to make 2 cups.

title: pie crust
directions: Work together flour, Crisco and salt.
Combine in separate bowl flour and milk and stir together.
Add to above ingredients and work together for dough ball.

title: garlic cheese log
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Soften cream cheese and roll of bacon-cheese spread.
Shape into a log.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Roll log in mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with pimiento. Yield:
One 6-inch cheese log.

title: popsicles
directions: Put Kool-Aid in pitcher.
Put in sugar.
Put in water.
Stir it up.
We pour it in the popsicles.
Put on Kool-Aid tops.
Put them in the freezer.
Then we can eat them.

title: bride cake
directions: Mix and sift first 4 ingredients.
Cream shortening until soft and airy, working in sugar at this time.
Sift in flour mixture in several stages, then vanilla mixed in thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, two at a time.
Fold each 2 into batter separately, finally stirring gently.
Turn into 10-inch layer pan not greased but lined with plain paper.
Bake at 325° 1 hour or until tests done.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Cut up peppers, onion, tomatoes and crabmeat.
Mix together; add dressing to taste.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut partially frozen dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices slightly overlapping on pizza sheet. Press edge to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly.
Loosen cookie from sheet and then allow to finish cooling on sheet.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Cut into slices or wedges with pizza cutter.

title: baby pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use a miniature muffin pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, stick butter and flour.
Distribute evenly into bottom of each muffin shell.
Place 1/2 the nuts over this mixture.
Beat together the egg, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Place on top of nuts.
Top each muffin with the remaining nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 18 to 20 minutes.

title: ricky chicky
directions: Take chicken breast sprinkle generous amount of black pepper on both sides of the breasts (the more the spicier).
Pound pepper into chicken breast with glass.
Fill glass halfway with honey; fill the rest the way with teriyaki sauce.
Cover the bottom of frying pan with about 1/4 inch of olive oil.
Heat oil and place chicken in oil and cook 4 minutes each side.
With one minute left on the last side pour sauce into pan and cook for 1 minute.
Take pan off heat; remove chicken from pan and spoon sauce on the breast.
Good served on a bed of rice.

title: quick chicken 'n' dumplins'
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the chicken, broth, margarine and milk.
Pinch biscuits into small pieces and drop into boiling mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until thick.

title: texas chili
directions: Heat suet in large saucepan until 1/2 cup fat is rendered.
Add meat cubes and cook stirring until meat loses its red color. Sprinkle with garlic and chili powder and flour, stirring.
Crush cumin and oregano and add to meat.
Add beef broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer at least 4 hours.
The meat should be fork-tender when done.
Great served over brown rice.
This is my mother's recipe.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer 10 to 15 minutes or until fluffy.
Spoon batter into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Makes a large cake.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Mix Eagle Brand with pudding mix.
Add vanilla and milk gradually.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Place wafers on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top each wafer with a banana slice.
Cover with 1/2 of mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs over the top.

title: tangy vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in cruet or jar.
Chill for at least 1/2 hour.
Shake well before dressing salad.

title: cinnamon 'n' spice apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add apples; toss to coat apples.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix in a large microwave measuring cup first 4 ingredients. Cook 4 minutes on high. Stir well and cook for 4 more minutes. Add vanilla and 1 Tbsp. butter and
mix well. Cook 4 more minutes. Remove from microwave and add 1/2 tsp. baking soda. Mix well and pour into well buttered cookie sheet. Cool.

title: asparagus dip
directions: Drain asparagus and mix all together in blender.
Great with vegetables.

title: banana cake(tube pan)
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place separated graham crackers on foil.
Melt butter; add brown sugar. Stir constantly while cooking 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add nuts.
Spread on graham crackers and bake for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: nestle toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs in large mixer bowl on high speed until foamy. Beat in flour, granulated sugar and brown sugar.

Beat in butter. Stir in morsels and nuts. Spoon into pie shell. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside edge and center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sweet and spicy barbecue ribs
directions: In a large bowl, combine catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce, hickory-flavored salt, pepper and garlic.
Cover; let stand at room temperature for 30
minutes or refrigerate for up to 5 days.

title: beef stew
