directions: Brown beef tips in saucepan, then cover with water and add bouillon cubes. Cook to a boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours, making sure to keep water in pan (or until meat is tender). Add Mrs. Dash when adding bouillon cubes. Peel potatoes and cut them; add to stew. Open can of Veg-All. Drain and add. Cook to boiling until potatoes are tender.

title: swiss and turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with extra croutons, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place cooked, drained ground beef in the bottom of 8-inch square pan or baking dish.
Spread mushroom soup (undiluted) evenly over meat.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over this.
Arrange Tater Tots in rows over cheese.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs and sesame seeds together.
Dip chicken in buttermilk and coat with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until chicken is brown and crispy.

title: super dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage bread
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw, but not rise.
Stretch out lengthwise on countertop, approximately 24-inches.
Roll out lengthwise and widthwise as much as possible.
Mix egg with enough Parmesan to make a paste and spread down center of the dough. Next, layer browned, drained sausage on the dough, followed by mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Stretch and bring sides of dough up to meet in the center.
Pinch and seal down entire length.
Put onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Curve to fit pan.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 20 minutes.

title: caramel cake delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Works great in 1/2 bun pans (school).
Sprinkle entire cake with chopped walnuts before baking.
Bake at 350° until done (do not overbake).
Serve warm or cool with a scoop of ice cream (vanilla) and top with caramel ice cream topping.
Heat caramel topping in microwave for a minute.
It makes it easy to spoon on the ice cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Brown meat. Heat oven to 350°.
Drain meat; stir in tomato sauce.
In baking dish layer cooked pasta, meat sauce and cheeses.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes; remove foil.
Bake 5 more minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: italian beef roll
directions: Pound the meat to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine all ingredients, except water.
Spread stuffing evenly over the meat; roll up and tie with a spring or roll in aluminum foil.
Place in baking pan or dish.
Add water to pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for a tossed salad.
Drain and rinse chilled beans.
Combine lettuce, diced tomatoes, onions, beans, grated cheese and Catalina dressing.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Add crushed corn chips and mix well before serving.
Serves 12.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice thin the flank steak.
Turn each piece on its side and pound until flat.

Mix the remaining 7 ingredients and marinate meat in sauce overnight or at least 10 hours, for best results. Lay each piece flat on aluminum foil and dry in oven (using just pilot) for 24 hours, turning occasionally.
You may turn oven on low occasionally, but just for a short period of time and be sure to check it often.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over and press down, then coconut, then chocolate, then butterscotch pieces.
Pour milk over all.
Sprinkle nuts and press lightly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, cheddar cheese and Ranch dressing mix by hand or in a food processor.
Form into a ball.
Roll in sunflower seeds.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix in order given except the last 4 ingredients. Form into 60 meat balls (size of grapes).
Put in baking dish.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix the above, then toss with the following dressing.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add in order and beat in: egg, salt, soda and persimmons.
Mix together baking powder and flour and stir into liquid mixture.
Stir in nuts by hand.
Bake at 375° on a greased cookie sheet for approximately 12 minutes.
Great dipped in Cool Whip.

title: mexican meal
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Cook macaroni; drain. Add all ingredients to ground beef; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cherry watermelon pickles
directions: Remove green skin and pink flesh of watermelon from rind.
Cut rind into 1-inch squares.
Place in saucepan and cover with water; add salt.
Set aside for 4 hours.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain again.
Add enough water to cover; bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 10 minutes, remove from heat and drain thoroughly.
Combine sugar and vinegar in 5 to 6-quart pan.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag and add to sugar-vinegar mixture.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add rind.
Cool and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove rind.
Bring syrup to a boil. Add rind and cherries; let boil 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Pack rind and cherry mixture in sterilized jars, covering completely with hot syrup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns to separate.
Mix all ingredients except crumbs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Add some grated cheese on top if you like.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie with strawberry puree
directions: Cool pie crust.
Put cream cheese in a bowl and blend on low with electric mixer.
Slowly add sweetened evaporated milk.
Mix on high until smooth.
Add lemon juice and blend well.
Pour into cooled pie crust and chill.

title: party potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and boil until tender.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add hot potatoes, gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut half the meat from the bones, brown in hot fat.
Add remaining meat and bone to the cold water, add browned meat, onion and salt.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue cooking 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: el dorado surprise
directions: Crumble beef and cook with onion, garlic and green pepper; drain fat.
Add olives, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes over medium heat.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, cottage cheese and green chilies.
Shred cheese.
Crush all but 1 cup chips.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer beef, sour cream mixture, chips and cheese.
Repeat layering; cover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Drop temperature to 325°, uncover and bake 30 minutes. Garnish with remaining chips.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Grease pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: belgian raisin bread
directions: Mix scalded milk, butter, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs.
Add a cup of flour, then yeast, then the rest of the flour.
Add raisins.
Knead; let rise to double in size.
Knead. Shape into loaves.
Put into loaf pans.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then sit back and enjoy.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add marshmallows.
When cool, add drained pineapple and bananas.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour, butter and egg until thick. Cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on top.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil over moderate heat.
Add the beef, season it with 1/4 teaspoon of the salt and 1/8 teaspoon of the pepper, and cook for 5 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the beef to a 5-quart Dutch oven.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls and pinch creases together.
Build a crust edge around border of pan.
Bake crust until done and let cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain.
Mix onion, chicken soup, sour cream and croutons.
Place in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water on shortening.
Stir until melted.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Add beaten eggs, yeast and dry ingredients. Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, turn on floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush with butter before cooking.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop on cookie sheets and press down with a cup.
Sprinkle with jello.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain fat.
Add package taco seasoning; mix in good.
Set aside to cool.
Cut up lettuce and tomato.
Add beans and cheese, then add meat.
Add dressing and chips just before you serve.

title: sweet-ricotta pie
directions: Beat ingredients together with a beater.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for one hour.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender. Mix with mayonnaise. Set aside. Split breast butterfly style; lay

2 beef circles slightly overlapping inside the split. Add a spoonful of mushroom mixture and spoonful of Parmesan cheese. Close and wrap a strip of bacon around each breast to secure and place in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.

After all breasts are stuffed and placed in dish, combine mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour over breasts and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve with noodles, rice or potatoes. You cannot believe how good this is.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine salt, sugar and butter. Heat milk and pour over this mixture until butter melts. Add eggs (beaten) and yeast; mix well. Then add remaining flour gradually. If dough becomes dry, add small amount of milk. Dough should be sticky. After mixing all ingredients, place in large bowl and cover until dough rises double bulk. Then roll out dough. Cut into squares. Place in pan. Let rise from 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: salmon and cheese puff
directions: Beat eggs and reserve 1 tablespoon for glazing.
Add diced cheese, herbs, salt and pepper to beaten eggs.
Drain salmon and flake.
Add to cheese mixture along with parsley, bread crumbs and mayonnaise.
Roll pastry into 12 inch x 18 inch rectangle.
Cut in half.
Place half on biscuit tray and pile on mixture.
Glaze the edge and cover with second piece of pastry.
Glaze over top with egg.
Press down edges with fork and "stab" top of pie a few times.
Bake in moderate oven (350°F/180°C) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber "raita"
directions: Mix grated cucumber, yogurt, spices and salt together.
Heat the oil.
When hot, add mustard seed.
When the seed starts making a crackling noise, remove from heat and pour over the mix.
Mix well; garnish with cilantro.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, green pepper, celery, garlic, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Remove fat.
Add tomatoes, paste and sauce.
Cover just to top with water.
Cook over medium heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg and molasses. Beat well.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat and Italian sausage.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and carrots.
Drain.
Add oregano, basil, pepper, peeled tomatoes and tomato paste.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate overnight.
Beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Layer.
Layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese mixture and sauce.
Repeat layers.

title: pralines
directions: Place in large pan and boil all ingredients, except pecans, until a soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla and stir until the mixture starts to thicken.
Add pecans and spoon onto wax paper.
Will make 25 to 30 pralines.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to the directions on the box.
Drain spinach thoroughly.
Shred cheese, chop onion and bacon.
Mix together eggs and milk.
In a bowl combine cheese, onion, bacon (grease drained) and spinach.
Add egg/milk mixture.
Pour into pie pans.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 hungry people.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix as listed and bake at 400°.
This will make 12 muffins.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Warm soups and cheese until cheese is melted.
Mix with chicken and noodles.
Heat in baking dish in oven at 350° until warm.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg; add milk.
Stir into dry ingredients; mix well.
Add melted oleo.

title: rice, cauliflower and broccoli toss
directions: Add sugar and vinegar to dressing.
Pour dressing over vegetables and rice.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: guilt-free red potato salad(heart healthy)
directions: Wash, peel and cube potatoes.
Place in 3-quart microwave dish with 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover and cook on High power for 6 minutes.
Drain in colander and cover with 6 ice cubes to speed cooling.
While potatoes are cooking, cook eggs for 10 minutes. While eggs are cooking, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar, pepper, onion and celery in a 3-quart salad bowl.
When eggs are finished cooking, rinse under cold water, peel and chop into dressing mixture.
Add cooled potatoes, stir just to blend and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat milk and egg together and mix into dry ingredients with oil.
Stir well.
Place wooden popsicle stick in one end of hot dog, about 1-inch deep.
Roll in batter; fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: more casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain and mix with tomato sauce.
Add browned ground beef and onion.
Mix half cheese in mixture.
Put in baking dish.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 300° oven until cheese on top is melted, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tofu scrambled
directions: Mash tofu fine.
Saute onions in oil until soft.
Add tofu, parsley flakes, salt and turmeric.
Mix well.
Saute for 3 or 4 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bombay brussels sprouts
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except sprouts.
Pour over hot sprouts.
Makes 3 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients separately.
Then combine, bake at 350 degrees for 1 and 1/4 hours in greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: stuffed potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, onions, garlic butter, regular butter, bacon, salt, and black pepper in large soup pot.
Cook until potatoes are tender but not mushy. Add half and half, chives, and cheese spread.
Cook until cheese is completely melted.
Combine sour cream and flour in small bowl and mix well. Reduce heat to low and stir in sour cream mixture.
Continue cooking until soup begins to thicken.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine the ingredients together and drop onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Skin chicken and place in baking dish.
Mix soup, sherry and sour cream.
Cover chicken with sliced mushrooms.
Cover chicken and mushrooms with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix following box directions.
Pour into a greased 13x9-inch pan.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: In medium bowl, add crushed pineapple to dry pudding mix. Stir until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix together and refrigerate.

title: peach crisp
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Place peach slices in a greased pie pan.
Stir in cereal, apple juice concentrate and cinnamon.
Top with dabs of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 small servings.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: With a spoon, mix in a large bowl the flour and sugar.
In a saucepan combine the cocoa, water and butter and bring to a boil. Pour into flour and sugar.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir.
Add this mixture plus vanilla and eggs to mixture in a large bowl. Stir well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: mayflower pumpkin pie(a new england recipe)
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar.
Add nuts.
Press mixture firmly into the bottom of pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chile pepper water
directions: Puree the first 6 ingredients in a blender.
Bring 1 1/4 cups water to a boil.
Add puree and return to a boil.
Cool.
When cooled, transfer to a bottle or glass jar and refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Shake before using for a hotter sauce.
Red chile peppers are used, but green can be substituted.

title: biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and sugar; set aside for 10 minutes. Mix sugar, shortening and salt with scalded milk; cool to lukewarm.
Combine yeast and milk mixture; add flour and mix well. Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Soak fruits overnight in the Port wine and vanilla.
In the morning, cream the butter and eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix very well.
Be sure to put a pan of boiling water on the floor of the oven to keep the cakes from drying out during the long baking time.
Line the pans with wax paper, greasing pan and paper and fill 3/4 full with the batter. Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Let set in pans for ten minutes. Turn cakes out on racks and cool leaving the paper on.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce in bottom of a large bowl.
Add peas over lettuce, then layer onion, eggs, cheese and top with Bac*Os.
Pour Ranch dressing (whole bottle) over salad.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Makes a complete meal.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread, tomatoes, bell pepper, celery, onion and bacon.
Blend
in
mayonnaise.
Chill
until serving time. Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine and mix.
Take pie from oven and cover with sour cream mixture.
Put back in oven at 350° for 5 minutes until firm.
Let cool and top with fruit topping.
Yields 2 cakes.

title: houston style chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and allow to simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: miss jessie's easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water just until tender.
Drain. Arrange in casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Layer sliced chicken on top. Combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on a baking sheet and bake until brown at 350°.
Makes 75 to 100 balls.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, onion, garlic, corn flakes and eggs.
Season to taste.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Combine remaining ingredients in heavy skillet; simmer 5 minutes.
Place meat balls in the sauce.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Cool.
Refrigerate until fat hardens.
Remove and discard fat.
Reheat to serve. Makes approximately 65 servings.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into chunks.
Grate cheese.
Cut tortillas into triangles.
In a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan, layer chips, chicken, Cheddar cheese, Jack cheese and more chips, Cheddar cheese and Jack cheese.
Mix soup and spread.
Add salsa on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice 5 minutes less than package directions.
Mix with remaining ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan, blend salt, sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and coloring.
Pack apples into hot jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Fill with hot syrup.
Use knife to remove air bubbles.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes for quarts, 15 for pints.
Each quart will make a 9-inch pie.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a nonstick skillet and saute green chiles and onion over low heat for two minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, garlic powder and oregano.
Add salt.
Simmer, uncovered, about thirty minutes until thick.

title: christmas fruit bread
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast cakes and 6 cups flour to make batter.
Let rise.
Add sugar, eggs, melted butter and salt.
Cover fruit and nuts with flour and mix well.
Fold into batter with other seasonings and flour.
Knead to a stiff dough. Let rise until double in bulk, then cut and put in pans.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 5 loaves.
Brush loaves with butter when done and removed from pans.
Cool and wrap.

title: ice cream roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and slowly mix into egg mixture at low speed until batter is smooth.
Grease a jelly roll pan and line with waxed paper.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and turn upside down on towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove paper; roll up in towel.
Let cool. Unroll and spread with 1 quart ice cream.
Roll again; wrap in foil and freeze.
Garnish with chocolate sauce or cherry.

title: sunshine broccoli
directions: Mix together.
Pour dressing over mixture before serving.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: In large bowl, combine first five ingredients; set aside.

In microwave safe bowl, heat chips and oil on medium high 2 minutes. Stirring over. Microwave on high for 10 seconds; stir until smooth. Pour over cereal mixture and mix well. Spread onto three wax paper lined baking sheets. Cool and break apart. Stir into airtight container. Yields 5 quarts.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Combine. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in greased, wax-papered loaf pan.

title: chicken bake casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, vegetables, 1/4 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions until well blended.
Spread mixture into 8 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: crab and creamed corn soup
directions: Dice bacon and cook on low heat in a heavy soup kettle until almost all the fat is rendered.
Pour off rendered fat and add corn, pepper, celery, onion, bay leaves and water.
Cook, stirring often, for 10 to 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt butter and stir in the flour; when bubbly, add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook, continuing to stir, until steaming hot; add corn mixture and crab. Mix well and season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Cook and stir 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan; top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Combine margarine and stuffing.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil together water and sugar to dissolve.
Cool; add orange juice, pineapple juice and mashed bananas.
Mix together.
Divide into six 1-quart containers.
Freeze.
Before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale to each container.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Drain oranges thoroughly.
Prepare muffin mix as directed on package.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Arrange orange segments on batter and sprinkle with streusel mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix apples, pineapple and peanuts together.
Add to cream mixture. Serve the same day.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together.
May be marinated several hours or overnight.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook onion and squash until soft; salt.
Drain and mash; add margarine, soup, crackers and cheese.
Add sour cream last.
Put in casserole dish.
Put dressing mix on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak raisins in wine for 30 minutes.
Peel and dice cucumbers. Mix all ingredients together and chill at least one hour.
Line 4 salad plates with lettuce leaf and spoon cucumber mixture on each plate.
Serves 4.

title: luncheon meat and noodles(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan. Blend in flour, salt and pepper; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thick.
Add meat, noodles and mustard.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle over noodles.
Bake for about 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Simmer together.
Pour into casserole.
Place cheese over meat.
Add olives.
Add noodles, then tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Place covered casserole in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Blend eggs and seasonings in blender at high speed.
Blend thoroughly.
Add lemon juice, starting at high speed.
Remove filler cap cover and slowly pour in half the oil.
Add vinegar, then rest of oil, running blender until thoroughly mixed.
This is almost like bought mayonnaise.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
In a separate bowl, mix cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Over the chicken, sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic salt and chili powder and also the onions.
Next, spread soup mixture over the chicken.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over soup mixture. Crush Doritos and sprinkle over cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Trim off excess fat from roast; sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in crock-pot. Add the vegetables, bay leaves, rosemary and thyme to slow cooker. Add the broth. Cover and cook on low 8 1/2 to 9 hours or until beef is tender. Remove beef to serving platter. Arrange vegetables around it. Remember to discard the 2 bay leaves.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk to yeast mixture.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Work shortening into flour until mealy, then add yeast and milk.
Mix well.
Keep in a covered bowl in fridge.
Roll and shape into biscuits.

title: popcorn with cheese
directions: Pop corn.
Place popped corn in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine; mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese and salt; mix.
Heat 8 to 10 minutes at 325°; stir often.
Each cup contains 170 calories.
Yields 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook to hard ball stage.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda; stir.
Then spread on buttered surface. Loosen with knife when cool.
Break into pieces.

title: candy mints
directions: Roll in long strips and cut with scissors or cut into shapes. Can pour in mold if thinner.
Good for parties.

title: terri's blonde brownies
directions: Note:
For something a little different, omit chocolate chips.

title: eggplant parmigiana(yields 4 to 6 portions)
directions: Combine the Ricotta cheese, eggs, Parmesan and parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine tomato sauce and crushed garlic.
Spread half cup of sauce mixture in bottom of large deep dish casserole pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in small amount of water.
Add salt to taste. Add celery, onion and carrot.
Cook potatoes, celery, onion and carrot down.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add milk, butter, parsley, dill and pepper.
Heat and don't boil.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook celery, pepper and onion in bacon drippings until soft. Add other ingredients and cook for 1 hour.
Add shrimp. Serve over rice.

title: maryland oven barbecued chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield:
8 generous servings.
(This recipe can be made ahead of time and frozen until ready to serve, just heat and eat.)

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.

title: guacamole salad dip
directions: Mix together and top with a few chopped tomatoes.

title: georgia cracker pie
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients.
Put in a greased pie pan.
Cook 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with ranch dressing.
Form into a ball.
Roll the ball in pecans pressing lightly.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: reese bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar a little at a time (you will need the full pound) until smooth and spreadable.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: christmas tea
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Add orange juice, lemonade and red food coloring.
Never boil concentrate, but dilute 1/3 of the concentrate with 2/3 boiling water.

title: french fried cheese bits
directions: Cut cheese into 1/2 to 1 inch cubes.
Dip in milk and then flour.
Roll the cubes in egg and then in fine crumbs.
Fry cheese bits in deep Crisco heated to about 365° (or when an inch cube of bread browns in 60 seconds).
Fry about one minute, or until as brown as desired.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve very hot.

title: fiesta french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered jar; shake well. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Beat eggs moderately; add lemon juice and combine with cheese mixture.
Place vanilla wafers in paper baking cups.
Pour mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. When cool, top with cherry, blueberry or apricot canned pie filling.
Makes 12.

title: ned's christmas egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Stir and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 generously.

title: chicken with tarragon
directions: Remove backbones from chicken halves.
Reserve.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in a heavy skillet large enough to hold whole chicken.
Add chicken, skin side down.
Surround with gizzard, heart, neck and backbone.
Cook about 10 minutes, until golden brown on skin side.
Turn and cook 5 minutes longer. Remove chicken and set aside.
To skillet add shallots and cook briefly.
Add tarragon and wine.
Stir to dissolve the brown particles that cling to bottom of skillet.
Stir in water.
Return chicken to skillet, skin side up and cover.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking, basting after 5 minutes, until tender and glazed.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans and coat with corn meal. Combine milk and water.
Heat on high 3 to 4 minutes (probe set at 125°).
Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl. Blend in remaining flour.
Mix until stiff (sticky). Divide dough. Cover and raise for 45 minutes.
Cook, one at a time, on High (600 to 700 watts) for 6 to 6 1/2 minutes, turning once.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan. Slice thinly and toast before serving.
Just like an English muffin.
Delicious!

title: sorghum spice cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; add eggs and sorghum.
Sift together flour, soda and spices and add to mixture.
Chill dough a few hours or overnight.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: southwest turkey pie(using basic marinara sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook onion and 1/2 cup green pepper in heavy skillet.
Crumble turkey into skillet.
Add spices and cook until meat is no longer pink.
Add
sauce, chilies, olives, corn and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add half the cheese. Place in a greased baking dish.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips, then add peanut butter and Rice Chex.
Pour into paper bag and add powdered sugar.
Shake to coat.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix both mixtures together, then add raisins, nuts and apples.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, peanuts and Reeses's pieces or M&M's together. Melt together in heavy saucepan:
cooking oil, margarine and marshmallows.
Boil this mixture 1 minute.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Spray angel food cake pan or Bundt pan with Pam. Pour mixture in and let set for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out to desired thickness and use cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 17 minutes or until light brown.
Do not roll out too thick. Frost when cool.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs good.
Add sugar, salt and milk and beat good.
Cook pie shell a little.
Then pour mixture in the shell.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Then cook 30 more minutes, uncovered.

title: fried puppies
directions: Pat out bread dough, cutting 2 to 3 inch pieces.
Wrap dough pieces around each wiener.
Deep fat fry in shortening.
Turn evenly to brown.

title: shrimp glace
directions: Boil tomato soup.
Add cream cheese and stir until well blended.
Add onion, celery, shrimp, mayonnaise and gelatine mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour in well-greased mold and chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and flavorings.
Beat well. Dredge raisins in 1/2 cup flour and add to mixture.
Sift remaining flour with other dry ingredients and add to mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 40 two-inch cookies.

title: garden salad
directions: Drain the corn, beans and peas. Add the celery, onion and pepper; mix thoroughly. Make dressing from the last 5 ingredients. Pour the dressing over the vegetables and refrigerate overnight. Will keep for days in the refrigerator.

title: crazy cake
directions: Spray 13 x 10-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan.
This batter is thin and makes a thin cake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with ready made white sour cream frosting.

title: sandwiches
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Place mixture on a bun, then slice of ham and slice of Swiss cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Sift sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Add sugar mixture slowly, until stiff, glossy peaks. Spread over bottom and sides of a well-greased 9-inch pie plate, bottom 1/4-inch thick, sides 1-inch thick.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°, or until brown.
Cool away from drafts (will crack).
Open oven door and let cool in oven about 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour; blend in egg yolks, milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook on medium-high heat.
Cook until thickened.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in a deep casserole bowl until all bananas are used.
Pour sauce over this and chill.
